files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AbortController
files.Summary: The AbortController interface represents a controller object that allows you to abort one or more Web requests as and when desired.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AbortSignal
files.Summary: The AbortSignal interface represents a signal object that allows you to communicate with an asynchronous operation (such as a fetch request) and abort it if required via an object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AbsoluteOrientationSensor
files.Summary: The AbsoluteOrientationSensor interface of the Sensor APIs describes the device's physical orientation in relation to the Earth's reference coordinate system.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AbstractRange
files.Summary: The AbstractRange abstract interface is the base class upon which all DOM range types are defined. A range is an object that indicates the start and end points of a section of content within the document.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Accelerometer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The Accelerometer interface of the Sensor APIs provides on each reading the acceleration applied to the device along all three axes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AesCbcParams
files.Summary: The AesCbcParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into , , , or , when using the AES-CBC algorithm.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AesCtrParams
files.Summary: The AesCtrParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into , , , or , when using the AES-CTR algorithm.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AesGcmParams
files.Summary: The AesGcmParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into , , , or , when using the AES-GCM algorithm.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AesKeyGenParams
files.Summary: The AesKeyGenParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into , when generating an AES key: that is, when the algorithm is identified as any of AES-CBC, AES-CTR, AES-GCM, or AES-KW.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AmbientLightSensor
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The AmbientLightSensor interface of the Sensor APIs returns the current light level or illuminance of the ambient light around the hosting device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AnalyserNode
files.Summary: The AnalyserNode interface represents a node able to provide real-time frequency and time-domain analysis information. It is an that passes the audio stream unchanged from the input to the output, but allows you to take the generated data, process it, and create audio visualizations.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Animation
files.Summary: The Animation interface of the Web Animations API represents a single animation player and provides playback controls and a timeline for an animation node or source.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AnimationEffect
files.Summary: The AnimationEffect interface of the Web Animations API is an interface representing animation effects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AnimationEvent
files.Summary: The AnimationEvent interface represents events providing information related to animations.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AnimationPlayState
files.Summary: The read-only Animation.playState property of the Web Animations API returns an enumerated value describing the playback state of an animation.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AnimationPlaybackEvent
files.Summary: The AnimationPlaybackEvent interface of the Web Animations API represents animation events.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AnimationReplaceState
files.Summary: The read-only Animation.replaceState property of the Web Animations API indicates whether the animation has been removed by the browser automatically after being replaced by another animation.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AnimationTimeline
files.Summary: The AnimationTimeline interface of the Web Animations API represents the timeline of an animation. This interface exists to define timeline features, inherited by other timeline types:

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Attr
files.Summary: The Attr interface represents one of an element's attributes as an object. In most situations, you will directly retrieve the attribute value as a string (e.g., ), but some cases may require interacting with Attr instances (e.g., ).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioBuffer
files.Summary: The AudioBuffer interface represents a short audio asset residing in memory, created from an audio file using the BaseAudioContext/decodeAudioData method, or from raw data using BaseAudioContext/createBuffer. Once put into an AudioBuffer, the audio can then be played by being passed into an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioBufferSourceNode
files.Summary: The AudioBufferSourceNode interface is an which represents an audio source consisting of in-memory audio data, stored in an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioContext
files.Summary: The AudioContext interface represents an audio-processing graph built from audio modules linked together, each represented by an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioData
files.Summary: The AudioData interface of the WebCodecs API represents an audio sample.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioDecoder
files.Summary: The AudioDecoder interface of the 'WebCodecs API' decodes chunks of audio.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioDestinationNode
files.Summary: The AudioDestinationNode interface represents the end destination of an audio graph in a given context usually the speakers of your device. It can also be the node that will "record" the audio data when used with an OfflineAudioContext.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioEncoder
files.Summary: The AudioEncoder interface of the WebCodecs API encodes objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioListener
files.Summary: The AudioListener interface represents the position and orientation of the unique person listening to the audio scene, and is used in audio spatialization. All s spatialize in relation to the AudioListener stored in the attribute.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioNode
files.Summary: The AudioNode interface is a generic interface for representing an audio processing module.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioParam
files.Summary: The Web Audio API's AudioParam interface represents an audio-related parameter, usually a parameter of an (such as ).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioParamDescriptor
files.Summary: The AudioParamDescriptor dictionary of the Web Audio API specifies properties for objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioParamMap
files.Summary: The AudioParamMap interface of the Web Audio API represents an iterable and read-only set of multiple audio parameters.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioProcessingEvent
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
The AudioProcessingEvent interface of the Web Audio API represents events that occur when a input buffer is ready to be processed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioScheduledSourceNode
files.Summary: The AudioScheduledSourceNode interfacepart of the Web Audio APIis a parent interface for several types of audio source node interfaces which share the ability to be started and stopped, optionally at specified times. Specifically, this interface defines the and methods, as well as the AudioScheduledSourceNode.Ended_event event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioSinkInfo
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The AudioSinkInfo interface of the {{domxref("Web Audio API", "Web Audio API", "", "nocode")}} represents information describing an 's sink ID, retrieved via .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioTrack
files.Summary: The AudioTrack interface represents a single audio track from one of the HTML media elements, audio or video.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioTrackList
files.Summary: The AudioTrackList interface is used to represent a list of the audio tracks contained within a given HTML media element, with each track represented by a separate object in the list.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioWorklet
files.Summary: The AudioWorklet interface of the Web Audio API is used to supply custom audio processing scripts that execute in a separate thread to provide very low latency audio processing.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioWorkletGlobalScope
files.Summary: The AudioWorkletGlobalScope interface of the Web Audio API represents a global execution context for user-supplied code, which defines custom -derived classes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioWorkletNode
files.Summary:
NOTE
Although the interface is available outside secure contexts, the property is not, thus custom s cannot be defined outside them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AudioWorkletProcessor
files.Summary: The AudioWorkletProcessor interface of the Web Audio API represents an audio processing code behind a custom . It lives in the and runs on the Web Audio rendering thread. In turn, an based on it runs on the main thread.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AuthenticatorAssertionResponse
files.Summary: The AuthenticatorAssertionResponse interface of the Web Authentication API contains a digital signature from the private key of a particular WebAuthn credential. The relying party's server can verify this signature to authenticate a user, for example when they sign in.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AuthenticatorAttestationResponse
files.Summary: The AuthenticatorAttestationResponse interface of the Web Authentication API is the result of a WebAuthn credential registration. It contains information about the credential that the server needs to perform WebAuthn assertions, such as its credential ID and public key.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.AuthenticatorResponse
files.Summary: The AuthenticatorResponse interface of the Web Authentication API is the base interface for interfaces that provide a cryptographic root of trust for a key pair. The child interfaces include information from the browser such as the challenge origin and either may be returned from .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BackgroundFetchEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The BackgroundFetchEvent interface of the {{domxref('Background Fetch API', "", "", "nocode")}} is the event type for background fetch events dispatched on the {{domxref("ServiceWorkerGlobalScope", "service worker global scope", "", "nocode")}}.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BackgroundFetchManager
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The BackgroundFetchManager interface of the 'Background Fetch API' is a map where the keys are background fetch IDs and the values are objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BackgroundFetchRecord
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The BackgroundFetchRecord interface of the 'Background Fetch API' represents an individual request and response.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BackgroundFetchRegistration
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The BackgroundFetchRegistration interface of the 'Background Fetch API' represents an individual background fetch.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BackgroundFetchUpdateUIEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The BackgroundFetchUpdateUIEvent interface of the 'Background Fetch API' is an event type for the ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.Backgroundfetchsuccess_event and ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.Backgroundfetchfail_event events, and provides a method for updating the title and icon of the app to inform a user of the success or failure of a background fetch.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BarProp
files.Summary: The BarProp interface of the Document Object Model represents the web browser user interface elements that are exposed to scripts in web pages. Each of the following interface elements are represented by a BarProp object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BarcodeDetector
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The BarcodeDetector interface of the 'Barcode Detection API' allows detection of linear and two dimensional barcodes in images.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BaseAudioContext
files.Summary: The BaseAudioContext interface of the Web Audio API acts as a base definition for online and offline audio-processing graphs, as represented by and respectively. You wouldn't use BaseAudioContext directly you'd use its features via one of these two inheriting interfaces.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BatteryManager
files.Summary: The BatteryManager interface of the {{domxref("Battery Status API", "", "", "nocode")}} provides information about the system's battery charge level. The method returns a promise that resolves with a BatteryManager interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BeforeInstallPromptEvent
files.Summary:
CAUTION
Non-standard
The BeforeInstallPromptEvent is the interface of the Window.Beforeinstallprompt_event event fired at the object before a user is prompted to "install" a website to a home screen on mobile.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BeforeUnloadEvent
files.Summary: The BeforeUnloadEvent interface represents the event object for the Window/beforeunload_event event, which is fired when the current window, contained document, and associated resources are about to be unloaded.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BiquadFilterNode
files.Summary: The BiquadFilterNode interface represents a simple low-order filter, and is created using the BaseAudioContext/createBiquadFilter method. It is an that can represent different kinds of filters, tone control devices, and graphic equalizers. A BiquadFilterNode always has exactly one input and one output.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Blob
files.Summary: The Blob interface represents a blob, which is a file-like object of immutable, raw data; they can be read as text or binary data, or converted into a so its methods can be used for processing the data.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BlobEvent
files.Summary: The BlobEvent interface of the MediaStream Recording API represents events associated with a . These blobs are typically, but not necessarily, associated with media content.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Bluetooth
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The Bluetooth interface of the Web Bluetooth API provides methods to query Bluetooth availability and request access to devices.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BluetoothCharacteristicProperties
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The BluetoothCharacteristicProperties interface of the Web Bluetooth API provides the operations that are valid on the given 'BluetoothRemoteGATTCharacteristic'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BluetoothDevice
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The BluetoothDevice interface of the Web Bluetooth API represents a Bluetooth device inside a particular script execution
environment.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BluetoothRemoteGATTCharacteristic
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The BluetoothRemoteGattCharacteristic interface of the Web Bluetooth API represents a GATT Characteristic, which is a basic data element that provides further information about a peripheral's service.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BluetoothRemoteGATTDescriptor
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The BluetoothRemoteGATTDescriptor interface of the Web Bluetooth API provides a GATT Descriptor,
which provides further information about a characteristic's value.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BluetoothRemoteGATTServer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The BluetoothRemoteGATTServer interface of the Web Bluetooth API represents a GATT
Server on a remote device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BluetoothRemoteGATTService
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The BluetoothRemoteGATTService interface of the Web Bluetooth API represents a
service provided by a GATT server, including a device, a list of referenced services,
and a list of the characteristics of this service.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BluetoothUUID
files.Summary:
The BluetoothUUID interface of the Web Bluetooth API provides a way to look up Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) values by name in the
registry maintained by the Bluetooth SIG.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.BroadcastChannel
files.Summary: The BroadcastChannel interface represents a named channel that any {{glossary("browsing context")}} of a given {{glossary("origin")}} can subscribe to. It allows communication between different documents (in different windows, tabs, frames or iframes) of the same origin. Messages are broadcasted via a BroadcastChannel/message_event event fired at all BroadcastChannel objects listening to the channel, except the object that sent the message.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ByteLengthQueuingStrategy
files.Summary: The ByteLengthQueuingStrategy interface of the Streams API provides a built-in byte length queuing strategy that can be used when constructing streams.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CDATASection
files.Summary:
The CDATASection interface represents a CDATA section
that can be used within XML to include extended portions of unescaped text.
When inside a CDATA section, the symbols < and & don't need escaping
as they normally do.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSPViolationReportBody
files.Summary: The CSPViolationReportBody interface is an extension of the Reporting API that represents the body of a Content Security Policy (CSP) violation report.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSS
files.Summary: The CSS interface holds useful CSS-related methods. No objects with this interface are implemented: it contains only static methods and is therefore a utilitarian interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSAnimation
files.Summary: The CSSAnimation interface of the 'Web Animations API' represents an object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSConditionRule
files.Summary: An object implementing the CSSConditionRule interface represents a single condition CSS at-rule, which consists of a condition and a statement block.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSContainerRule
files.Summary: The CSSContainerRule interface represents a single CSS rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSCounterStyleRule
files.Summary: The CSSCounterStyleRule interface represents an at-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSFontFaceRule
files.Summary: The CSSFontFaceRule interface represents an at-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSFontFeatureValuesRule
files.Summary: The CSSFontFeatureValuesRule interface represents an at-rule, letting developers assign for each font face a common name to specify features indices to be used in font-variant-alternates.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSFontPaletteValuesRule
files.Summary: The CSSFontPaletteValuesRule interface represents an at-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSGroupingRule
files.Summary: The CSSGroupingRule interface of the CSS Object Model represents any CSS at-rule that contains other rules nested within it.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSImageValue
files.Summary: The CSSImageValue interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents values for properties that take an image, for example 'background-image', 'list-style-image', or 'border-image-source'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSImportRule
files.Summary: The CSSImportRule interface represents an at-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSKeyframeRule
files.Summary: The CSSKeyframeRule interface describes an object representing a set of styles for a given keyframe. It corresponds to the contents of a single keyframe of a at-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSKeyframesRule
files.Summary: The CSSKeyframesRule interface describes an object representing a complete set of keyframes for a CSS animation. It corresponds to the contents of a whole at-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSKeywordValue
files.Summary: The CSSKeywordValue interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API creates an object to represent CSS keywords and other identifiers.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSLayerBlockRule
files.Summary: The CSSLayerBlockRule represents a block rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSLayerStatementRule
files.Summary: The CSSLayerStatementRule represents a {{cssxref("")}} statement rule. Unlike , it doesn't contain other rules and merely defines one or several layers by providing their names.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSMathInvert
files.Summary: The CSSMathInvert interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents a CSS 'calc' used as calc(1 / <value>). It inherits properties and methods from its parent 'CSSNumericValue'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSMathMax
files.Summary: The CSSMathMax interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents the CSS {{CSSXref('max','max()')}} function. It inherits properties and methods from its parent 'CSSNumericValue'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSMathMin
files.Summary: The CSSMathMin interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents the CSS {{CSSXref('min','min()')}} function. It inherits properties and methods from its parent 'CSSNumericValue'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSMathNegate
files.Summary: The CSSMathNegate interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API negates the value passed into it. It inherits properties and methods from its parent 'CSSNumericValue'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSMathProduct
files.Summary: The CSSMathProduct interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents the result obtained by calling 'CSSNumericValue.Add', 'CSSNumericValue.Sub', or 'CSSNumericValue.ToSum' on 'CSSNumericValue'. It inherits properties and methods from its parent 'CSSNumericValue'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSMathSum
files.Summary: The CSSMathSum interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents the result obtained by calling 'CSSNumericValue.Add', 'CSSNumericValue.Sub', or 'CSSNumericValue.ToSum' on 'CSSNumericValue'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSMathValue
files.Summary: The CSSMathValue interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API a base class for classes representing complex numeric values.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSMatrixComponent
files.Summary: The CSSMatrixComponent interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents the matrix() and matrix3d() values of the individual {{CSSXRef('transform')}} property in CSS. It inherits properties and methods from its parent 'CSSTransformValue'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSMediaRule
files.Summary: The CSSMediaRule interface represents a single CSS rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSNamespaceRule
files.Summary: The CSSNamespaceRule interface describes an object representing a single CSS at-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSNestedDeclarations
files.Summary: The CSSNestedDeclarations interface of the CSS Rule API is used to group nested s.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSNumericArray
files.Summary: The CSSNumericArray interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API contains a list of objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSNumericValue
files.Summary: The CSSNumericValue interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents operations that all numeric values can perform.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSPageDescriptors
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The CSSPageDescriptors interface represents a CSS declaration block for an @pageat-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSPageRule
files.Summary: CSSPageRule represents a single CSS @page rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSPerspective
files.Summary: The CSSPerspective interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents the perspective() value of the individual {{CSSXRef('transform')}} property in CSS. It inherits properties and methods from its parent 'CSSTransformValue'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSPositionTryDescriptors
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The CSSPositionTryDescriptors interface defines properties that represent the list of CSS descriptors that can be set in the body of a @position-tryat-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSPositionTryRule
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The CSSPositionTryRule interface describes an object representing a @position-tryat-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSPropertyRule
files.Summary: The CSSPropertyRule interface of the CSS Properties and Values API represents a single CSS rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSPseudoElement
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The CSSPseudoElement interface represents a pseudo-element that may be the target of an event or animated using the 'Web Animations API'. Instances of this interface may be obtained by calling 'Element.Pseudo'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSRotate
files.Summary: The CSSRotate interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents the rotate value of the individual {{CSSXRef('transform')}} property in CSS. It inherits properties and methods from its parent 'CSSTransformValue'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSRule
files.Summary: The CSSRule interface represents a single CSS rule. There are several types of rules which inherit properties from CSSRule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSRuleList
files.Summary: A CSSRuleList represents an ordered collection of read-only objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSScale
files.Summary: The CSSScale interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents the scale() and scale3d() values of the individual {{CSSXRef('transform')}} property in CSS. It inherits properties and methods from its parent 'CSSTransformValue'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSScopeRule
files.Summary: The CSSScopeRule interface of the CSS Object Model represents a CSS at-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSSkew
files.Summary: The CSSSkew interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API is part of the 'CSSTransformValue' interface. It represents the skew() value of the individual 'transform' property in CSS.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSSkewX
files.Summary: The CSSSkewX interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents the skewX() value of the individual {{CSSXRef('transform')}} property in CSS. It inherits properties and methods from its parent .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSSkewY
files.Summary: The CSSSkewY interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents the skewY() value of the individual {{CSSXRef('transform')}} property in CSS. It inherits properties and methods from its parent .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSStartingStyleRule
files.Summary: The CSSStartingStyleRule interface of the CSS Object Model represents a CSS at-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSStyleDeclaration
files.Summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration interface represents an object that is a CSS declaration block, and exposes style information and various style-related methods and properties.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSStyleRule
files.Summary: The CSSStyleRule interface represents a single CSS style rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSStyleSheet
files.Summary: The CSSStyleSheet interface represents a single CSS stylesheet, and lets you inspect and modify the list of rules contained in the stylesheet. It inherits properties and methods from its parent, .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSStyleValue
files.Summary: The CSSStyleValue interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API is the base class of all CSS values accessible through the Typed OM API. An instance of this class may be used anywhere a string is expected.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSSupportsRule
files.Summary: The CSSSupportsRule interface represents a single CSS at-rule.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSTransformComponent
files.Summary: The CSSTransformComponent interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API is part of the 'CSSTransformValue' interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSTransformValue
files.Summary: The CSSTransformValue interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents transform-list values as used by the CSS 'transform' property.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSTransition
files.Summary: The CSSTransition interface of the 'Web Animations API' represents an object used for a CSS Transition.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSTranslate
files.Summary: The CSSTranslate interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents the translate() value of the individual {{CSSXRef('transform')}} property in CSS. It inherits properties and methods from its parent 'CSSTransformValue'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSUnitValue
files.Summary: The CSSUnitValue interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents values that contain a single unit type. For example, "42px" would be represented by a CSSNumericValue.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSUnparsedValue
files.Summary: The CSSUnparsedValue interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API represents property values that reference custom properties. It consists of a list of string fragments and variable references.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CSSVariableReferenceValue
files.Summary: The CSSVariableReferenceValue interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API allows you to create a custom name for a built-in CSS value. This object functionality is sometimes called a "CSS variable" and serves the same purpose as the var function. The custom name must begin with two dashes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Cache
files.Summary: The Cache interface provides a persistent storage mechanism for / object pairs that are cached in long lived memory. How long a Cache object lives is browser dependent, but a single origin's scripts can typically rely on the presence of a previously populated Cache object. Note that the Cache interface is exposed to windowed scopes as well as workers. You don't have to use it in conjunction with service workers, even though it is defined in the service worker spec.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CacheStorage
files.Summary: The CacheStorage interface represents the storage for objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CanMakePaymentEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The CanMakePaymentEvent interface of the {{domxref("Payment Handler API", "", "", "nocode")}} is the event object for the ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.Canmakepayment_event event, fired on a payment app's service worker to check whether it is ready to handle a payment. Specifically, it is fired when the merchant website calls the constructor.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CanvasCaptureMediaStreamTrack
files.Summary: The CanvasCaptureMediaStreamTrack interface of the {{domxref("Media Capture and Streams API", "", "", "nocode")}} represents the video track contained in a being generated from a {{HTMLElement("canvas")}} following a call to .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CanvasGradient
files.Summary: The CanvasGradient interface represents an opaque object describing a gradient. It is returned by the methods CanvasRenderingContext2D.CreateLinearGradient, CanvasRenderingContext2D.CreateConicGradient or CanvasRenderingContext2D.CreateRadialGradient.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CanvasPattern
files.Summary: The CanvasPattern interface represents an opaque object describing a pattern, based on an image, a canvas, or a video, created by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.CreatePattern method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CanvasRenderingContext2D
files.Summary:
The CanvasRenderingContext2D interface, part of the Canvas API, provides the 2D rendering context for the drawing surface of a canvas element.
It is used for drawing shapes, text, images, and other objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CaptureController
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The CaptureController interface provides methods that can be used to further manipulate a capture session separate from its initiation via .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CaretPosition
files.Summary:
The CaretPosition interface represents the caret position, an indicator for the text insertion point.
You can get a CaretPosition using the method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ChannelMergerNode
files.Summary: The ChannelMergerNode interface, often used in conjunction with its opposite, , reunites different mono inputs into a single output. Each input is used to fill a channel of the output. This is useful for accessing each channels separately, e.g. for performing channel mixing where gain must be separately controlled on each channel.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ChannelSplitterNode
files.Summary: The ChannelSplitterNode interface, often used in conjunction with its opposite, , separates the different channels of an audio source into a set of mono outputs. This is useful for accessing each channel separately, e.g. for performing channel mixing where gain must be separately controlled on each channel.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ChapterInformation
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The ChapterInformation interface of the {{domxref("Media Session API", "", "", "nocode")}} represents the metadata for an individual chapter of a media resource (i.e. a video or audio file).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CharacterBoundsUpdateEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The CharacterBoundsUpdateEvent interface is a DOM event that represents a request from the operating system to know the bounds of certain characters within an editable region that's attached to an instance.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CharacterData
files.Summary: The CharacterData abstract interface represents a object that contains characters. This is an abstract interface, meaning there aren't any objects of type CharacterData: it is implemented by other interfaces like , , , or , which aren't abstract.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ChildNode
files.Summary: Element is the most general base class from which all element objects (i.e. objects that represent elements) in a inherit. It only has methods and properties common to all kinds of elements. More specific classes inherit from Element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Client
files.Summary: The Client interface represents an executable context such as a , or a . clients are represented by the more-specific . You can get Client/WindowClient objects from methods such as and .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ClientType
files.Summary:
The type read-only property of the
interface indicates the type of client the service worker is controlling.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Clients
files.Summary: The Clients interface provides access to objects. Access it via {{domxref("ServiceWorkerGlobalScope", "self")}}.clients within a service worker.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Clipboard
files.Summary:
The Clipboard interface of the Clipboard API provides read and write access to the contents of the system clipboard.
This allows a web application to implement cut, copy, and paste features.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ClipboardEvent
files.Summary: The ClipboardEvent interface of the Clipboard API represents events providing information related to modification of the clipboard, that is Element/cut_event, Element/copy_event, and Element/paste_event events.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ClipboardItem
files.Summary: The ClipboardItem interface of the Clipboard API represents a single item format, used when reading or writing clipboard data using and respectively.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CloseEvent
files.Summary: A CloseEvent is sent to clients using WebSockets when the connection is closed. This is delivered to the listener indicated by the WebSocket object's onclose attribute.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CloseWatcher
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The CloseWatcher interface allows a custom UI component with open and close semantics to respond to device-specific close actions in the same way as a built-in component.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Comment
files.Summary: The Comment interface represents textual notations within markup; although it is generally not visually shown, such comments are available to be read in the source view.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CompositionEvent
files.Summary: The DOM CompositionEvent represents events that occur due to the user indirectly entering text.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CompressionStream
files.Summary: The CompressionStream interface of the 'Compression Streams API' is an API for compressing a stream of data.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ConstantSourceNode
files.Summary: The ConstantSourceNode interfacepart of the Web Audio APIrepresents an audio source (based upon ) whose output is single unchanging value. This makes it useful for cases in which you need a constant value coming in from an audio source. In addition, it can be used like a constructible by automating the value of its or by connecting another node to it; see Controlling multiple parameters with ConstantSourceNode.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ContactAddress
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The ContactAddress interface of the Contact Picker API represents a physical address. Instances of this interface are retrieved from the address property of the objects returned by .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ContactsManager
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The ContactsManager interface of the Contact Picker API allows users to select entries from their contact list and share limited details of the selected entries with a website or application.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ContentIndex
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The ContentIndex interface of the Content Index API allows developers to register their offline enabled content with the browser.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ContentIndexEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The ContentIndexEvent interface of the content index defines the object used to represent the ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.Contentdelete_event event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ContentVisibilityAutoStateChangeEvent
files.Summary: The ContentVisibilityAutoStateChangeEvent interface is the event object for the Element/contentvisibilityautostatechange_event event, which fires on any element with {{cssxref("content-visibility", "content-visibility: auto")}} set on it when it starts or stops being relevant to the user and skipping its contents.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ConvolverNode
files.Summary: The ConvolverNode interface is an that performs a Linear Convolution on a given , often used to achieve a reverb effect. A ConvolverNode always has exactly one input and one output.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CookieChangeEvent
files.Summary: The CookieChangeEvent interface of the {{domxref("Cookie Store API", "", "", "nocode")}} is the event type of the CookieStore/change_event event fired at a when any cookies are created or deleted.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CookieStore
files.Summary: The CookieStore interface of the {{domxref("Cookie Store API", "", "", "nocode")}} provides methods for getting and setting cookies asynchronously from either a page or a service worker.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CookieStoreManager
files.Summary: The CookieStoreManager interface of the {{domxref("Cookie Store API", "", "", "nocode")}} allows service workers to subscribe to cookie change events. Call on a particular service worker registration to receive change events.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CountQueuingStrategy
files.Summary: The CountQueuingStrategy interface of the Streams API provides a built-in chunk counting queuing strategy that can be used when constructing streams.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Credential
files.Summary: The Credential interface of the Credential Management API provides information about an entity (usually a user) normally as a prerequisite to a trust decision.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CredentialsContainer
files.Summary: The CredentialsContainer interface of the Credential Management API exposes methods to request credentials and notify the user agent when events such as successful sign in or sign out happen. This interface is accessible from 'Navigator.Credentials'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Crypto
files.Summary:
The Crypto interface represents basic cryptography features available in the current context.
It allows access to a cryptographically strong random number generator and to cryptographic primitives.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CryptoKey
files.Summary: The CryptoKey interface of the Web Crypto API represents a cryptographic {{glossary("key")}} obtained from one of the methods , , , or .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CryptoKeyPair
files.Summary: The CryptoKeyPair dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents a key pair for an asymmetric cryptography algorithm, also known as a public-key algorithm.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CustomElementRegistry
files.Summary: The CustomElementRegistry interface provides methods for registering custom elements and querying registered elements. To get an instance of it, use the property.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CustomEvent
files.Summary: The CustomEvent interface represents events initialized by an application for any purpose.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.CustomStateSet
files.Summary: The CustomStateSet interface of the Document Object Model stores a list of states for an autonomous custom element, and allows states to be added and removed from the set.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMException
files.Summary: The DOMException interface represents an abnormal event (called an exception) that occurs as a result of calling a method or accessing a property of a web API. This is how error conditions are described in web APIs.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMImplementation
files.Summary: The DOMImplementation interface represents an object providing methods which are not dependent on any particular document. Such an object is returned by the property.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMMatrix
files.Summary:
The DOMMatrix interface represents 44 matrices, suitable for 2D and 3D operations including rotation and translation. It is a mutable version of the interface.
The interface is available inside web workers.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMMatrixReadOnly
files.Summary: The DOMMatrixReadOnly interface represents a read-only 44 matrix, suitable for 2D and 3D operations. The interface which is based upon DOMMatrixReadOnlyadds mutability, allowing you to alter the matrix after creating it.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMParser
files.Summary:
The DOMParser interface provides
the ability to parse XML or HTML source code from a
string into a DOM .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMPoint
files.Summary: A DOMPoint object represents a 2D or 3D point in a coordinate system; it includes values for the coordinates in up to three dimensions, as well as an optional perspective value. DOMPoint is based on but allows its properties' values to be changed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMPointReadOnly
files.Summary: The DOMPointReadOnly interface specifies the coordinate and perspective fields used by to define a 2D or 3D point in a coordinate system.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMQuad
files.Summary: A DOMQuad is a collection of four DOMPoints defining the corners of an arbitrary quadrilateral. Returning DOMQuads lets getBoxQuads() return accurate information even when arbitrary 2D or 3D transforms are present. It has a handy bounds attribute returning a DOMRectReadOnly for those cases where you just want an axis-aligned bounding rectangle.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMRect
files.Summary: A DOMRect describes the size and position of a rectangle.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMRectList
files.Summary: The DOMRectList interface represents a collection of objects, typically used to hold the rectangles associated with a particular element, like bounding boxes returned by methods such as . It provides access to each rectangle in the list via its index, along with a length property that indicates the total number of rectangles in the list.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMRectReadOnly
files.Summary: The DOMRectReadOnly interface specifies the standard properties (also used by ) to define a rectangle whose properties are immutable.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMStringList
files.Summary: The DOMStringList interface is a legacy type returned by some APIs and represents a non-modifiable list of strings (DOMString).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMStringMap
files.Summary: The DOMStringMap interface is used for the HTMLElement.Dataset attribute, to represent data for custom attributes added to elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DOMTokenList
files.Summary: The DOMTokenList interface represents a set of space-separated tokens. Such a set is returned by or , and many others.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DataTransfer
files.Summary: The DataTransfer object is used to hold any data transferred between contexts, such as a drag and drop operation, or clipboard read/write. It may hold one or more data items, each of one or more data types.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DataTransferItem
files.Summary: The DataTransferItem object represents one drag data item. During a drag operation, each has a property which contains a of drag data items. Each item in the list is a DataTransferItem object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DataTransferItemList
files.Summary: The DataTransferItemList object is a list of objects representing items being dragged. During a drag operation, each has a property and that property is a DataTransferItemList.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DecompressionStream
files.Summary: The DecompressionStream interface of the 'Compression Streams API' is an API for decompressing a stream of data.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope
files.Summary: The DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope object (the global scope) is accessible through the keyword. Some additional global functions, namespaces objects, and constructors, not typically associated with the worker global scope, but available on it, are listed in the JavaScript Reference. See also: Functions available to workers.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DelayNode
files.Summary: The DelayNode interface represents a delay-line; an audio-processing module that causes a delay between the arrival of an input data and its propagation to the output.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DelegatedInkTrailPresenter
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The DelegatedInkTrailPresenter interface of the Ink API provides the ability to instruct the OS-level compositor to render ink strokes between pointer event dispatches.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DeprecationReportBody
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The DeprecationReportBody interface of the Reporting API represents the body of a deprecation report.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DeviceMotionEvent
files.Summary: The DeviceMotionEvent interface of the {{domxref("Device Orientation Events", "", "", "nocode")}} provides web developers with information about the speed of changes for the device's position and orientation.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DeviceMotionEventAcceleration
files.Summary: The DeviceMotionEventAcceleration interface of the {{domxref("Device Orientation Events", "", "", "nocode")}} provides information about the amount of acceleration the device is experiencing along all three axes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DeviceMotionEventRotationRate
files.Summary: A DeviceMotionEventRotationRate interface of the {{domxref("Device Orientation Events", "", "", "nocode")}} provides information about the rate at which the device is rotating around all three axes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DeviceOrientationEvent
files.Summary: The DeviceOrientationEvent interface of the {{domxref("Device Orientation Events", "", "", "nocode")}} provides web developers with information from the physical orientation of the device running the web page.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Document
files.Summary: The Document interface represents any web page loaded in the browser and serves as an entry point into the web page's content, which is the DOM tree.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DocumentFragment
files.Summary: The DocumentFragment interface represents a minimal document object that has no parent.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DocumentPictureInPicture
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The DocumentPictureInPicture interface of the {{domxref("Document Picture-in-Picture API", "Document Picture-in-Picture API", "", "nocode")}} is the entry point for creating and handling document picture-in-picture windows.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DocumentPictureInPictureEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The DocumentPictureInPictureEvent interface of the {{domxref("Document Picture-in-Picture API", "Document Picture-in-Picture API", "", "nocode")}} is the event object for the DocumentPictureInPicture/enter_event event, which fires when the Picture-in-Picture window is opened.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DocumentReadyState
files.Summary:
The Document.readyState property describes the loading state of the .
When the value of this property changes, a Document/readystatechange_event event fires on the object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DocumentTimeline
files.Summary: The DocumentTimeline interface of the Web Animations API represents animation timelines, including the default document timeline (accessed via ).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DocumentType
files.Summary: The DocumentType interface represents a containing a doctype.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DocumentVisibilityState
files.Summary:
The Document.visibilityState
read-only property returns the visibility of the document. It can be used to check whether the document is in the background or in a minimized window, or is otherwise not visible to the user.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DragEvent
files.Summary: The DragEvent interface is a DOM event that represents a drag and drop interaction. The user initiates a drag by placing a pointer device (such as a mouse) on the touch surface and then dragging the pointer to a new location (such as another DOM element). Applications are free to interpret a drag and drop interaction in an application-specific way.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.DynamicsCompressorNode
files.Summary: The DynamicsCompressorNode interface provides a compression effect, which lowers the volume of the loudest parts of the signal in order to help prevent clipping and distortion that can occur when multiple sounds are played and multiplexed together at once. This is often used in musical production and game audio. DynamicsCompressorNode is an that has exactly one input and one output.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EcKeyGenParams
files.Summary: The EcKeyGenParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into , when generating any elliptic-curve-based key pair: that is, when the algorithm is identified as either of ECDSA or ECDH.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EcKeyImportParams
files.Summary: The EcKeyImportParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into or , when generating any elliptic-curve-based key pair: that is, when the algorithm is identified as either of ECDSA or ECDH.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EcdhKeyDeriveParams
files.Summary: The EcdhKeyDeriveParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into and , when using the ECDH or X25519 algorithms.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EcdsaParams
files.Summary: The EcdsaParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into or when using the ECDSA algorithm.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EditContext
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The EditContext interface represents the text edit context of an element that was made editable by using the {{domxref("EditContext API", "", "", "nocode")}}.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Element
files.Summary: Element is the most general base class from which all element objects (i.e. objects that represent elements) in a inherit. It only has methods and properties common to all kinds of elements. More specific classes inherit from Element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ElementInternals
files.Summary: The ElementInternals interface of the Document Object Model gives web developers a way to allow custom elements to fully participate in HTML forms. It provides utilities for working with these elements in the same way you would work with any standard HTML form element, and also exposes the Accessibility Object Model to the element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EncodedAudioChunk
files.Summary: The EncodedAudioChunk interface of the 'WebCodecs API' represents a chunk of encoded audio data.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EncodedAudioChunkType
files.Summary: The type read-only property of the interface returns a value indicating whether the audio chunk is a key chunk, which does not relying on other frames for decoding.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EncodedVideoChunk
files.Summary: The EncodedVideoChunk interface of the 'WebCodecs API' represents a chunk of encoded video data.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EncodedVideoChunkType
files.Summary: The type read-only property of the interface returns a value indicating whether the video chunk is a key chunk, which does not rely on other frames for decoding.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ErrorEvent
files.Summary: The ErrorEvent interface represents events providing information related to errors in scripts or in files.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Event
files.Summary: The Event interface represents an event which takes place on an EventTarget.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EventCounts
files.Summary: The EventCounts interface of the Performance API provides the number of events that have been dispatched for each event type.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EventSource
files.Summary: The EventSource interface is web content's interface to server-sent events.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EventTarget
files.Summary:
The EventTarget interface is implemented by objects that can receive events and may have listeners for them.
In other words, any target of events implements the three methods associated with this interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ExtendableCookieChangeEvent
files.Summary: The ExtendableCookieChangeEvent interface of the {{domxref("Cookie Store API", "", "", "nocode")}} is the event type passed to ServiceWorkerGlobalScope/cookiechange_event event fired at the when any cookie changes occur which match the service worker's cookie change subscription list. A cookie change event consists of a cookie and a type. (either "changed" or "deleted")

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ExtendableEvent
files.Summary: The ExtendableEvent interface extends the lifetime of the install and activate events dispatched on the global scope as part of the service worker lifecycle. This ensures that any functional events (like ) are not dispatched until it upgrades database schemas and deletes the outdated cache entries.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ExtendableMessageEvent
files.Summary: The ExtendableMessageEvent interface of the Service Worker API represents the event object of a ServiceWorkerGlobalScope/message_event event fired on a service worker (when a message is received on the from another context) extends the lifetime of such events.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.EyeDropper
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The EyeDropper interface represents an instance of an eyedropper tool that can be opened and used by the user to select colors from the screen.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FederatedCredential
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The FederatedCredential interface of the Credential Management API provides information about credentials from a federated identity provider. A federated identity provider is an entity that a website trusts to correctly authenticate a user, and that provides an API for that purpose. OpenID Connect is an example of a federated identity provider framework.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FederatedCredentialInit
files.Summary: The FederatedCredentialInit dictionary represents the object passed to as the value of the federated option: that is, when creating a object representing a credential associated with a federated identify provider.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Fence
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The Fence interface of the {{domxref("Fenced Frame API", "Fenced Frame API", "", "nocode")}} contains several functions relevant to fencedframe functionality.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FencedFrameConfig
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The FencedFrameConfig interface represents the navigation of a fencedframe, i.e. what content will be displayed in it.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FetchEvent
files.Summary: This is the event type for fetch events dispatched on the {{domxref("ServiceWorkerGlobalScope", "service worker global scope", "", 1)}}. It contains information about the fetch, including the request and how the receiver will treat the response. It provides the method, which allows us to provide a response to this fetch.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.File
files.Summary: The File interface provides information about files and allows JavaScript in a web page to access their content.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileList
files.Summary: The FileList interface represents an object of this type returned by the files property of the HTML input element; this lets you access the list of files selected with the <input type="file"> element. It's also used for a list of files dropped into web content when using the drag and drop API; see the object for details on this usage.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileReader
files.Summary: The FileReader interface lets web applications asynchronously read the contents of files (or raw data buffers) stored on the user's computer, using or objects to specify the file or data to read.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileReaderSync
files.Summary: The FileReaderSync interface allows to read or objects synchronously. This interface is only available in workers as it enables synchronous I/O that could potentially block.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileSystem
files.Summary: The File and Directory Entries API interface FileSystem is used to represent a file system. These objects can be obtained from the property on any file system entry. Some browsers offer additional APIs to create and manage file systems, such as Chrome's Window.RequestFileSystem method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileSystemDirectoryEntry
files.Summary: The FileSystemDirectoryEntry interface of the File and Directory Entries API represents a directory in a file system. It provides methods which make it possible to access and manipulate the files in a directory, as well as to access the entries within the directory.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileSystemDirectoryHandle
files.Summary: The FileSystemDirectoryHandle interface of the {{domxref("File System API", "File System API", "", "nocode")}} provides a handle to a file system directory.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileSystemDirectoryReader
files.Summary: The FileSystemDirectoryReader interface of the File and Directory Entries API lets you access the -based objects (generally or ) representing each entry in a directory.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileSystemEntry
files.Summary: The FileSystemEntry interface of the File and Directory Entries API represents a single entry in a file system. The entry can be a file or a directory (directories are represented by the interface). It includes methods for working with filesincluding copying, moving, removing, and reading filesas well as information about a file it points toincluding the file name and its path from the root to the entry.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileSystemFileEntry
files.Summary: The FileSystemFileEntry interface of the File and Directory Entries API represents a file in a file system. It offers properties describing the file's attributes, as well as the method, which creates a object that can be used to read the file.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileSystemFileHandle
files.Summary: The FileSystemFileHandle interface of the {{domxref("File System API", "File System API", "", "nocode")}} represents a handle to a file system entry. The interface is accessed through the 'window.ShowOpenFilePicker' method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileSystemHandle
files.Summary: The FileSystemHandle interface of the 'File System API' is an object which represents a file or directory entry. Multiple handles can represent the same entry. For the most part you do not work with FileSystemHandle directly but rather its child interfaces 'FileSystemFileHandle' and 'FileSystemDirectoryHandle'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileSystemHandleKind
files.Summary:
The kind read-only property of the
interface returns the type of entry. This is
'file' if the associated entry is a file or 'directory'. It is
used to distinguish files from directories when iterating over the contents of a
directory.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileSystemSyncAccessHandle
files.Summary: The FileSystemSyncAccessHandle interface of the {{domxref("File System API", "File System API", "", "nocode")}} represents a synchronous handle to a file system entry.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FileSystemWritableFileStream
files.Summary: The FileSystemWritableFileStream interface of the {{domxref("File System API", "File System API", "", "nocode")}} is a 'WritableStream' object with additional convenience methods, which operates on a single file on disk. The interface is accessed through the 'FileSystemFileHandle.CreateWritable' method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FocusEvent
files.Summary: The FocusEvent interface represents focus-related events, including Element/focus_event, Element/blur_event, Element/focusin_event, and Element/focusout_event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FontData
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The FontData interface of the {{domxref("Local Font Access API", "Local Font Access API", "", "nocode")}} represents a single local font face.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FontFace
files.Summary: The FontFace interface of the CSS Font Loading API represents a single usable font face.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FontFaceSet
files.Summary: The FontFaceSet interface of the CSS Font Loading API manages the loading of font-faces and querying of their download status.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FontFaceSetLoadEvent
files.Summary: The FontFaceSetLoadEvent interface of the CSS Font Loading API represents events fired at a after it starts loading font faces.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FormData
files.Summary: The FormData interface provides a way to construct a set of key/value pairs representing form fields and their values, which can be sent using the Window/fetch, or methods. It uses the same format a form would use if the encoding type were set to "multipart/form-data".

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FormDataEvent
files.Summary: The FormDataEvent interface represents a formdata event such an event is fired on an object after the entry list representing the form's data is constructed. This happens when the form is submitted, but can also be triggered by the invocation of a constructor.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.FragmentDirective
files.Summary: The FragmentDirective interface is an object exposed to allow code to check whether or not a browser supports text fragments.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GM.Info.Script
files.Summary: An object containing data about the currently running script. See more detail below.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GM.Info
files.Summary: An object that exposes various information about Greasemonkey and the running User Script. Compatibility: Greasemonkey 0.9.16+

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GM
files.Summary: Greasemonkey API

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPU
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPU interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} is the starting point for using WebGPU. It can be used to return a from which you can request devices, configure features and limits, and more.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUAdapter
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUAdapter interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents a GPU adapter. From this you can request a , adapter info, features, and limits.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUAdapterInfo
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUAdapterInfo interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} contains identifying information about a .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUBindGroup
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUBindGroup interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} is based on a and defines a set of resources to be bound together in a group and how those resources are used in shader stages.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUBindGroupLayout
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUBindGroupLayout interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} defines the structure and purpose of related GPU resources such as buffers that will be used in a pipeline, and is used as a template when creating s.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUBuffer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUBuffer interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents a block of memory that can be used to store raw data to use in GPU operations.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUBufferMapState
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The mapState read-only property of the
interface represents the mapped state of the GPUBuffer.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUBufferUsage
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The usage read-only property of the
interface contains the {{glossary("bitwise flags")}} representing the allowed usages of the GPUBuffer.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUCanvasContext
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUCanvasContext interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents the WebGPU rendering context of a {{htmlelement("canvas")}} element, returned via an call with a contextType of "webgpu".

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUCommandBuffer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUCommandBuffer interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents a pre-recorded list of GPU commands that can be submitted to a for execution.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUCommandEncoder
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUCommandEncoder interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents a command encoder, used to encode commands to be issued to the GPU.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUCompilationInfo
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUCompilationInfo interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents an array of objects generated by the GPU shader module compiler to help diagnose problems with shader code.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUCompilationMessage
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUCompilationMessage interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents a single informational, warning, or error message generated by the GPU shader module compiler.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUCompilationMessageType
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The type read-only property of the
interface is an enumerated value representing the type of the message. Each type represents a different severity level.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUComputePassEncoder
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUComputePassEncoder interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} encodes commands related to controlling the compute shader stage, as issued by a . It forms part of the overall encoding activity of a .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUComputePipeline
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUComputePipeline interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents a pipeline that controls the compute shader stage and can be used in a .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUDevice
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUDevice interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents a logical GPU device. This is the main interface through which the majority of WebGPU functionality is accessed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUDeviceLostInfo
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUDeviceLostInfo interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents the object returned when the {{jsxref("Promise")}} resolves. This provides information as to why a device has been lost.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUError
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUError interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} is the base interface for errors surfaced by and the GPUDevice.Uncapturederror_event event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUExternalTexture
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUExternalTexture interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents a wrapper object containing an snapshot that can be used as a texture in GPU rendering operations.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUInternalError
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUInternalError interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} describes an application error indicating that an operation failed for a system or implementation-specific reason, even when all validation requirements were satisfied.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUOutOfMemoryError
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUOutOfMemoryError interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} describes an out-of-memory (oom) error indicating that there was not enough free memory to complete the requested operation.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUPipelineError
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUPipelineError interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} describes a pipeline failure. This is the value received when a {{jsxref("Promise")}} returned by a or call rejects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUPipelineErrorReason
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The reason read-only property of the
interface defines the reason the pipeline creation failed in a machine-readable way.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUPipelineLayout
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUPipelineLayout interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} defines the s used by a pipeline. s used with the pipeline during command encoding must have compatible s.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUQuerySet
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUQuerySet interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} is used to record the results of queries on passes, such as occlusion or timestamp queries.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUQueue
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUQueue interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} controls execution of encoded commands on the GPU.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPURenderBundle
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPURenderBundle interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents a container for pre-recorded bundles of commands.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPURenderBundleEncoder
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPURenderBundleEncoder interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} is used to pre-record bundles of commands.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPURenderPassEncoder
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPURenderPassEncoder interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} encodes commands related to controlling the vertex and fragment shader stages, as issued by a . It forms part of the overall encoding activity of a .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPURenderPipeline
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPURenderPipeline interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents a pipeline that controls the vertex and fragment shader stages and can be used in a or .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUSampler
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUSampler interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents an object that can control how shaders transform and filter texture resource data.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUShaderModule
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUShaderModule interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents an internal shader module object, a container for WGSL shader code that can be submitted to the GPU for execution by a pipeline.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUSupportedFeatures
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUSupportedFeatures interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} is a Set-like object that describes additional functionality supported by a .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUSupportedLimits
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUSupportedLimits interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} describes the limits supported by a .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUTexture
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUTexture interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents a container used to store 1D, 2D, or 3D arrays of data, such as images, to use in GPU rendering operations.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUTextureDimension
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The dimension read-only property of the
interface represents the dimension of the set of texels for each GPUTexture subresource.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUTextureFormat
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The format read-only property of the
interface represents the format of the GPUTexture.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUTextureUsage
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The usage read-only property of the
interface is the {{glossary("bitwise flags")}} representing the allowed usages of the GPUTexture.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUTextureView
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUTextureView interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} represents a view into a subset of the texture resources defined by a particular .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUUncapturedErrorEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUUncapturedErrorEvent interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} is the event object type for the GPUDevice.Uncapturederror_event event, used for telemetry and to report unexpected errors.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GPUValidationError
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GPUValidationError interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} describes an application error indicating that an operation did not pass the WebGPU API's validation constraints.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GainNode
files.Summary: The GainNode interface represents a change in volume. It is an audio-processing module that causes a given gain to be applied to the input data before its propagation to the output. A GainNode always has exactly one input and one output, both with the same number of channels.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Gamepad
files.Summary: The Gamepad interface of the Gamepad API defines an individual gamepad or other controller, allowing access to information such as button presses, axis positions, and id.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GamepadButton
files.Summary: The GamepadButton interface defines an individual button of a gamepad or other controller, allowing access to the current state of different types of buttons available on the control device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GamepadEvent
files.Summary: The GamepadEvent interface of the Gamepad API contains references to gamepads connected to the system, which is what the gamepad events Window.Gamepadconnected_event and Window.Gamepaddisconnected_event are fired in response to.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GamepadHand
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The hand read-only property of the interface returns an enum defining what hand the controller is being held in, or is most likely to be held in.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GamepadHapticActuator
files.Summary: The GamepadHapticActuator interface of the Gamepad API represents hardware in the controller designed to provide haptic feedback to the user (if available), most commonly vibration hardware.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GamepadPose
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The GamepadPose interface of the Gamepad API represents the pose of a WebVR controller at a given timestamp (which includes orientation, position, velocity, and acceleration information).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Geolocation
files.Summary: The Geolocation interface represents an object able to obtain the position of the device programmatically. It gives Web content access to the location of the device. This allows a website or app to offer customized results based on the user's location.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GeolocationCoordinates
files.Summary:
The GeolocationCoordinates interface represents the position and altitude of the device on Earth, as well as the accuracy with which these properties are calculated.
