The geographic position information is provided in terms of World Geodetic System coordinates (WGS84).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GeolocationPosition
files.Summary: The GeolocationPosition interface represents the position of the concerned device at a given time. The position, represented by a object, comprehends the 2D position of the device, on a spheroid representing the Earth, but also its altitude and its speed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GeolocationPositionError
files.Summary: The GeolocationPositionError interface represents the reason of an error occurring when using the geolocating device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.GravitySensor
files.Summary: The GravitySensor interface of the Sensor APIs provides on each reading the gravity applied to the device along all three axes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Gyroscope
files.Summary: The Gyroscope interface of the Sensor APIs provides on each reading the angular velocity of the device along all three axes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HID
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The HID interface provides methods for connecting to HID devices, listing attached HID devices and event handlers for connected HID devices.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HIDConnectionEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The HIDConnectionEvent interface of the WebHID API represents HID connection events, and is the event type passed to HID/connect_event and HID/disconnect_event event handlers when a device's connection state changes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HIDDevice
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The HIDDevice interface of the WebHID API represents a HID Device. It provides properties for accessing information about the device, methods for opening and closing the connection, and the sending and receiving of reports.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HIDInputReportEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The HIDInputReportEvent interface of the WebHID API is passed to HIDDevice.Inputreport_event event of HIDDevice when an input report is received from any associated HID device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLAllCollection
files.Summary: The HTMLAllCollection interface represents a collection of all of the document's elements, accessible by index (like an array) and by the element's id. It is returned by the property.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLAnchorElement
files.Summary: The HTMLAnchorElement interface represents hyperlink elements and provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the regular object interface that they inherit from) for manipulating the layout and presentation of such elements. This interface corresponds to <a> element; not to be confused with <link>, which is represented by HTMLLinkElement.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLAreaElement
files.Summary: The HTMLAreaElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the regular object interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of {{HtmlElement("area")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLAudioElement
files.Summary: The HTMLAudioElement interface provides access to the properties of audio elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLBRElement
files.Summary: The HTMLBRElement interface represents an HTML line break element ({{htmlelement("br")}}). It inherits from .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLBaseElement
files.Summary: The HTMLBaseElement interface contains the base URI for a document. This object inherits all of the properties and methods as described in the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLBodyElement
files.Summary: The HTMLBodyElement interface provides special properties (beyond those inherited from the regular interface) for manipulating {{HtmlElement("body")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLButtonElement
files.Summary: The HTMLButtonElement interface provides properties and methods (beyond the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating {{HTMLElement("button")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLCanvasElement
files.Summary: The HTMLCanvasElement interface provides properties and methods for manipulating the layout and presentation of canvas elements. The HTMLCanvasElement interface also inherits the properties and methods of the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLCollection
files.Summary: The HTMLCollection interface represents a generic collection (array-like object similar to Functions/arguments) of elements (in document order) and offers methods and properties for selecting from the list.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLDListElement
files.Summary: The HTMLDListElement interface provides special properties (beyond those of the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating definition list ({{HtmlElement("dl")}}) elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLDataElement
files.Summary: The HTMLDataElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating {{HTMLElement("data")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLDataListElement
files.Summary: The HTMLDataListElement interface provides special properties (beyond the object interface it also has available to it by inheritance) to manipulate {{ HTMLElement("datalist") }} elements and their content.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLDetailsElement
files.Summary: The HTMLDetailsElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating {{HTMLElement("details")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLDialogElement
files.Summary: The HTMLDialogElement interface provides methods to manipulate {{HTMLElement("dialog")}} elements. It inherits properties and methods from the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLDivElement
files.Summary: The HTMLDivElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating {{HtmlElement("div")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLElement
files.Summary: The HTMLElement interface represents any HTML element. Some elements directly implement this interface, while others implement it via an interface that inherits it.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLEmbedElement
files.Summary: The HTMLEmbedElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating {{HTMLElement("embed")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLFencedFrameElement
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The HTMLFencedFrameElement interface represents a fencedframe element in JavaScript and provides configuration properties.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLFieldSetElement
files.Summary: The HTMLFieldSetElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of {{ HTMLElement("fieldset") }} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLFontElement
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
Implements the document object model (DOM) representation of the font element. The HTML Font Element font defines the font size, font face and color of text.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLFormControlsCollection
files.Summary: The HTMLFormControlsCollection interface represents a collection of HTML form control elements, returned by the interface's property.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLFormElement
files.Summary: The HTMLFormElement interface represents a form element in the DOM. It allows access toand, in some cases, modification ofaspects of the form, as well as access to its component elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLFrameSetElement
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
The HTMLFrameSetElement interface provides special properties (beyond those of the regular interface they also inherit) for manipulating {{HTMLElement("frameset")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLHRElement
files.Summary: The HTMLHRElement interface provides special properties (beyond those of the interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating {{HTMLElement("hr")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLHeadElement
files.Summary: The HTMLHeadElement interface contains the descriptive information, or metadata, for a document. This object inherits all of the properties and methods described in the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLHeadingElement
files.Summary: The HTMLHeadingElement interface represents the different heading elements, <h1> through <h6>. It inherits methods and properties from the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLHtmlElement
files.Summary: The HTMLHtmlElement interface serves as the root node for a given HTML document. This object inherits the properties and methods described in the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLIFrameElement
files.Summary: The HTMLIFrameElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of inline frame elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLImageElement
files.Summary: The HTMLImageElement interface represents an HTML img element, providing the properties and methods used to manipulate image elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLInputElement
files.Summary: The HTMLInputElement interface provides special properties and methods for manipulating the options, layout, and presentation of input elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLLIElement
files.Summary: The HTMLLIElement interface exposes specific properties and methods (beyond those defined by regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating list elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLLabelElement
files.Summary: The HTMLLabelElement interface gives access to properties specific to {{HTMLElement("label")}} elements. It inherits methods and properties from the base interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLLegendElement
files.Summary: The HTMLLegendElement is an interface allowing to access properties of the {{HTMLElement("legend")}} elements. It inherits properties and methods from the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLLinkElement
files.Summary: The HTMLLinkElement interface represents reference information for external resources and the relationship of those resources to a document and vice versa (corresponds to <link> element; not to be confused with <a>, which is represented by HTMLAnchorElement). This object inherits all of the properties and methods of the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLMapElement
files.Summary: The HTMLMapElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the regular object interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of map elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLMarqueeElement
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
The HTMLMarqueeElement interface provides methods to manipulate marquee elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLMediaElement
files.Summary: The HTMLMediaElement interface adds to the properties and methods needed to support basic media-related capabilities that are common to audio and video.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLMenuElement
files.Summary:
The HTMLMenuElement interface provides additional properties (beyond those inherited from the interface) for manipulating a {{HTMLElement("menu")}} element.
<menu> is a semantic alternative to the ul element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLMetaElement
files.Summary:
The HTMLMetaElement interface contains descriptive metadata about a document provided in HTML as <meta> elements.
This interface inherits all of the properties and methods described in the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLModElement
files.Summary: The HTMLModElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular methods and properties available through the interface they also have available to them by inheritance) for manipulating modification elements, that is {{HTMLElement("del")}} and {{HTMLElement("ins")}}.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLOListElement
files.Summary: The HTMLOListElement interface provides special properties (beyond those defined on the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating ordered list elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLObjectElement
files.Summary: The HTMLObjectElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those on the interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of {{HTMLElement("object")}} element, representing external resources.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLOptGroupElement
files.Summary: The HTMLOptGroupElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular object interface they also have available to them by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of {{HTMLElement("optgroup")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLOptionElement
files.Summary: The HTMLOptionElement interface represents {{HTMLElement("option")}} elements and inherits all properties and methods of the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLOptionsCollection
files.Summary: The HTMLOptionsCollection interface represents a collection of <option> HTML elements (in document order) and offers methods and properties for selecting from the list as well as optionally altering its items. This object is returned only by the options property of select.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLOutputElement
files.Summary: The HTMLOutputElement interface provides properties and methods (beyond those inherited from ) for manipulating the layout and presentation of {{HTMLElement("output")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLParagraphElement
files.Summary: The HTMLParagraphElement interface provides special properties (beyond those of the regular object interface it inherits) for manipulating {{HTMLElement("p")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLParamElement
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
The HTMLParamElement interface provides special properties (beyond those of the regular object interface it inherits) for manipulating {{HTMLElement("param")}} elements, representing a pair of a key and a value that acts as a parameter for an {{HTMLElement("object")}} element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLPictureElement
files.Summary: The HTMLPictureElement interface represents a picture HTML element. It doesn't implement specific properties or methods.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLPreElement
files.Summary: The HTMLPreElement interface exposes specific properties and methods (beyond those of the interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating a block of preformatted text ({{HtmlElement("pre")}}).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLProgressElement
files.Summary: The HTMLProgressElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of {{HTMLElement("progress")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLQuoteElement
files.Summary: The HTMLQuoteElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating quoting elements, like {{HTMLElement("blockquote")}} and {{HTMLElement("q")}}, but not the {{HTMLElement("cite")}} element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLScriptElement
files.Summary: JavaScript files should be served with the text/javascriptMIME type, but browsers are lenient and block them only if the script is served with an image type (image/), video type (video/), audio type (audio/*), or text/csv. If the script is blocked, its element receives an HTMLElement/error_event event; otherwise, it receives a Window/load_event event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLSelectElement
files.Summary: The HTMLSelectElement interface represents a {{HTMLElement("select")}} HTML Element. These elements also share all of the properties and methods of other HTML elements via the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLSlotElement
files.Summary: The HTMLSlotElement interface of the Shadow DOM API enables access to the name and assigned nodes of an HTML slot element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLSourceElement
files.Summary: The HTMLSourceElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular object interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating {{htmlelement("source")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLSpanElement
files.Summary: The HTMLSpanElement interface represents a {{HTMLElement("span")}} element and derives from the interface, but without implementing any additional properties or methods.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLStyleElement
files.Summary: The HTMLStyleElement interface represents a {{HTMLElement("style")}} element. It inherits properties and methods from its parent, .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLTableCaptionElement
files.Summary: The HTMLTableCaptionElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating table {{HTMLElement("caption")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLTableCellElement
files.Summary: The HTMLTableCellElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of table cells, either header cells ({{HTMLElement("th")}}) or data cells ({{HTMLElement("td")}}), in an HTML document.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLTableColElement
files.Summary: The HTMLTableColElement interface provides properties for manipulating single or grouped table column elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLTableElement
files.Summary: The HTMLTableElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular object interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of tables in an HTML document.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLTableRowElement
files.Summary: The HTMLTableRowElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of rows in an HTML table.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLTableSectionElement
files.Summary: The HTMLTableSectionElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of sections, that is headers, footers and bodies ({{HTMLElement("thead")}}, {{HTMLElement("tfoot")}}, and {{HTMLElement("tbody")}}, respectively) in an HTML table.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLTemplateElement
files.Summary: The HTMLTemplateElement interface enables access to the contents of an HTML template element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLTextAreaElement
files.Summary: The HTMLTextAreaElement interface provides special properties and methods for manipulating the layout and presentation of textarea elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLTimeElement
files.Summary: The HTMLTimeElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating {{HTMLElement("time")}} elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLTitleElement
files.Summary: The HTMLTitleElement interface is implemented by a document's {{ HTMLElement( "title" )}}. This element inherits all of the properties and methods of the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLTrackElement
files.Summary: The HTMLTrackElement interface represents an HTML {{HTMLElement("track")}} element within the DOM. This element can be used as a child of either {{HTMLElement("audio")}} or {{HTMLElement("video")}} to specify a text track containing information such as closed captions or subtitles.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLUListElement
files.Summary: The HTMLUListElement interface provides special properties (beyond those defined on the regular interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating unordered list ({{HTMLElement("ul")}}) elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLUnknownElement
files.Summary: The HTMLUnknownElement interface represents an invalid HTML element and derives from the interface, but without implementing any additional properties or methods.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HTMLVideoElement
files.Summary: The list of supported media formats varies from one browser to the other. You should either provide your video in a single format that all the relevant browsers supports, or provide multiple video sources in enough different formats that all the browsers you need to support are covered.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HashChangeEvent
files.Summary: The HashChangeEvent interface represents events that fire when the fragment identifier of the URL has changed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Headers
files.Summary: The Headers interface of the Fetch API allows you to perform various actions on HTTP request and response headers. These actions include retrieving, setting, adding to, and removing headers from the list of the request's headers.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Highlight
files.Summary: The Highlight interface of the CSS Custom Highlight API is used to represent a collection of instances to be styled using the API.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HighlightRegistry
files.Summary:
The HighlightRegistry interface of the CSS Custom Highlight API is used to register objects to be styled using the API.
It is accessed via .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HighlightType
files.Summary: The type property of the interface is an enumerated {{jsxref("String")}} used to specify the meaning of the highlight. This allows assistive technologies, such as screen readers, to include this meaning when exposing the highlight to users.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.History
files.Summary: The History interface of the {{domxref("History API", "", "", "nocode")}} allows manipulation of the browser session history, that is the pages visited in the tab or frame that the current page is loaded in.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HkdfParams
files.Summary: The HkdfParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into , when using the HKDF algorithm.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HmacImportParams
files.Summary: The HmacImportParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into or , when generating a key for the HMAC algorithm.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.HmacKeyGenParams
files.Summary: The HmacKeyGenParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into , when generating a key for the HMAC algorithm.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBCursor
files.Summary:
NOTE
Not to be confused with which is just an IDBCursor interface with an additional value property.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBCursorDirection
files.Summary:
The direction read-only property of the
interface is a string that returns the
direction of traversal of the cursor (set using
for example). See the Value
section below for possible values.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBCursorWithValue
files.Summary: The IDBCursorWithValue interface of the IndexedDB API represents a cursor for traversing or iterating over multiple records in a database. It is the same as the , except that it includes the value property.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBDatabase
files.Summary: The IDBDatabase interface of the IndexedDB API provides a connection to a database; you can use an IDBDatabase object to open a transaction on your database then create, manipulate, and delete objects (data) in that database. The interface provides the only way to get and manage versions of the database.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBFactory
files.Summary: The IDBFactory interface of the IndexedDB API lets applications asynchronously access the indexed databases. The object that implements the interface is window.indexedDB. You open that is, create and access and delete a database with this object, and not directly with IDBFactory.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBIndex
files.Summary: IDBIndex interface of the IndexedDB API provides asynchronous access to an index in a database. An index is a kind of object store for looking up records in another object store, called the referenced object store. You use this interface to retrieve data.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBKeyRange
files.Summary: The IDBKeyRange interface of the IndexedDB API represents a continuous interval over some data type that is used for keys. Records can be retrieved from and objects using keys or a range of keys. You can limit the range using lower and upper bounds. For example, you can iterate over all values of a key in the value range AZ.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBObjectStore
files.Summary: The IDBObjectStore interface of the IndexedDB API represents an object store in a database. Records within an object store are sorted according to their keys. This sorting enables fast insertion, look-up, and ordered retrieval.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBOpenDBRequest
files.Summary: The IDBOpenDBRequest interface of the IndexedDB API provides access to the results of requests to open or delete databases (performed using and ), using specific event handler attributes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBRequest
files.Summary: The IDBRequest interface of the IndexedDB API provides access to results of asynchronous requests to databases and database objects using event handler attributes. Each reading and writing operation on a database is done using a request.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBRequestReadyState
files.Summary:
The readyState read-only property of the
interface returns the state of the request.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBTransaction
files.Summary: The IDBTransaction interface of the IndexedDB API provides a static, asynchronous transaction on a database using event handler attributes. All reading and writing of data is done within transactions. You use to start transactions, IDBTransaction to set the mode of the transaction (e.g. is it readonly or readwrite), and you access an to make a request. You can also use an IDBTransaction object to abort transactions.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBTransactionDurability
files.Summary:
The durability read-only property of the interface returns the durability hint the transaction was created with.
This is a hint to the user agent of whether to prioritize performance or durability when committing the transaction.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBTransactionMode
files.Summary:
The mode read-only property of the
interface returns the current mode for accessing the
data in the object stores in the scope of the transaction (i.e. is the mode to be
read-only, or do you want to write to the object stores?) The default value is
readonly.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IDBVersionChangeEvent
files.Summary: The IDBVersionChangeEvent interface of the IndexedDB API indicates that the version of the database has changed, as the result of an IDBOpenDBRequest.Upgradeneeded_event event handler function.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IIRFilterNode
files.Summary: The IIRFilterNode interface of the Web Audio API is a processor which implements a general infinite impulse response (IIR) filter; this type of filter can be used to implement tone control devices and graphic equalizers as well. It lets the parameters of the filter response be specified, so that it can be tuned as needed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IdentityCredential
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The IdentityCredential interface of the Federated Credential Management API (FedCM) represents a user identity credential arising from a successful federated sign-in.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IdentityCredentialRequestOptions
files.Summary: The IdentityCredentialRequestOptions dictionary represents the object passed to as the value of the identity option.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IdentityProvider
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The IdentityProvider interface of the Federated Credential Management (FedCM) API represents an identity provider (IdP) and provides access to related information and functionality.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IdleDeadline
files.Summary: The IdleDeadline interface is used as the data type of the input parameter to idle callbacks established by calling . It offers a method, , which lets you determine how much longer the user agent estimates it will remain idle and a property, , which lets you determine if your callback is executing because its timeout duration expired.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IdleDetector
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The IdleDetector interface of the 'idle_detection_api' provides methods and events for detecting user activity on a device or screen.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ImageBitmap
files.Summary: The ImageBitmap interface represents a bitmap image which can be drawn to a {{HTMLElement("canvas")}} without undue latency. It can be created from a variety of source objects using the Window.CreateImageBitmap or WorkerGlobalScope.CreateImageBitmap factory method. ImageBitmap provides an asynchronous and resource efficient pathway to prepare textures for rendering in WebGL.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ImageBitmapRenderingContext
files.Summary: The ImageBitmapRenderingContext interface is a canvas rendering context that provides the functionality to replace the canvas's contents with the given . Its context id (the first argument to or ) is "bitmaprenderer".

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ImageCapture
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The ImageCapture interface of the MediaStream Image Capture API provides methods to enable the capture of images or photos from a camera or other photographic device. It provides an interface for capturing images from a photographic device referenced through a valid .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ImageData
files.Summary: The ImageData interface represents the underlying pixel data of an area of a canvas element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ImageDecoder
files.Summary: The ImageDecoder interface of the 'WebCodecs API' provides a way to unpack and decode encoded image data.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ImageTrack
files.Summary: The ImageTrack interface of the 'WebCodecs API' represents an individual image track.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ImageTrackList
files.Summary: The ImageTrackList interface of the 'WebCodecs API' represents a list of image tracks.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Ink
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The Ink interface of the Ink API provides access to objects for the application to use to render ink strokes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.InkPresenter
files.Summary: The InkPresenter interface of the Ink API provides the ability to instruct the OS-level compositor to render ink strokes between pointer event dispatches.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.InputDeviceCapabilities
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The InputDeviceCapabilities interface of the {{domxref("InputDeviceCapabilities API", "Input Device Capabilities API", "", "nocode")}} provides information about the physical device or a group of related devices responsible for generating input events. Events caused by the same physical input device get the same instance of this object, but the converse isn't true. For example, two mice with the same capabilities in a system may appear as a single InputDeviceCapabilities instance.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.InputDeviceInfo
files.Summary: The InputDeviceInfo interface of the {{domxref("Media Capture and Streams API", "", "", "nocode")}} gives access to the capabilities of the input device that it represents.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.InputEvent
files.Summary: The InputEvent interface represents an event notifying the user of editable content changes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.InstallEvent
files.Summary: The parameter passed into an ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.Install_event event handler function, the InstallEvent interface represents an install action that is dispatched on the of a . As a child of , it ensures that functional events such as are not dispatched during installation.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IntersectionObserver
files.Summary: The IntersectionObserver interface of the Intersection Observer API provides a way to asynchronously observe changes in the intersection of a target element with an ancestor element or with a top-level document's 'viewport'. The ancestor element or viewport is referred to as the root.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.IntersectionObserverEntry
files.Summary: The IntersectionObserverEntry interface of the Intersection Observer API describes the intersection between the target element and its root container at a specific moment of transition.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.InterventionReportBody
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The InterventionReportBody interface of the Reporting API represents the body of an intervention report.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Keyboard
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The Keyboard interface of the {{domxref("Keyboard API", "", "", "nocode")}} provides functions that retrieve keyboard layout maps and toggle capturing of key presses from the physical keyboard.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.KeyboardEvent
files.Summary: KeyboardEvent objects describe a user interaction with the keyboard; each event describes a single interaction between the user and a key (or combination of a key with modifier keys) on the keyboard. The event type (Element/keydown_event, Element/keypress_event, or Element/keyup_event) identifies what kind of keyboard activity occurred.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.KeyboardLayoutMap
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The KeyboardLayoutMap interface of the {{domxref("Keyboard API", "", "", "nocode")}} is a read-only object with functions for retrieving the string associated with specific physical keys.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.KeyframeEffect
files.Summary: The KeyframeEffect interface of the Web Animations API lets us create sets of animatable properties and values, called keyframes. These can then be played using the constructor.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.LargestContentfulPaint
files.Summary: The LargestContentfulPaint interface provides timing information about the largest image or text paint before user input on a web page.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.LaunchParams
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The LaunchParams interface of the {{domxref("Launch Handler API", "Launch Handler API", "", "nocode")}} is used when implementing custom launch navigation handling in a PWA. When is invoked to set up the launch navigation handling functionality, the callback function inside setConsumer() is passed a LaunchParams object instance.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.LaunchQueue
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The LaunchQueue interface of the {{domxref("Launch Handler API", "Launch Handler API", "", "nocode")}} is available via the property. When a progressive web app (PWA) is launched with a launch_handlerclient_mode value of focus-existing, navigate-new, or navigate-existing, LaunchQueue provides access to functionality that allows custom launch navigation handling to be implemented in the PWA. This functionality is controlled by the properties of the object passed into the callback function.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.LayoutShift
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The LayoutShift interface of the Performance API provides insights into the layout stability of web pages based on movements of the elements on the page.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.LayoutShiftAttribution
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The LayoutShiftAttribution interface provides debugging information about elements which have shifted.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.LinearAccelerationSensor
files.Summary: The LinearAccelerationSensor interface of the Sensor APIs provides on each reading the acceleration applied to the device along all three axes, but without the contribution of gravity.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Location
files.Summary: The Location interface represents the location (URL) of the object it is linked to. Changes done on it are reflected on the object it relates to. Both the and interface have such a linked Location, accessible via and respectively.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Lock
files.Summary:
The Lock interface of the Web Locks API provides the name and mode of a lock.
This may be a newly requested lock that is received in the callback to 'LockManager.Request', or a record of an active or queued lock returned by 'LockManager.Query'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.LockManager
files.Summary: The LockManager interface of the Web Locks API provides methods for requesting a new 'Lock' object and querying for an existing Lock object. To get an instance of LockManager, call 'navigator.Locks'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.LockMode
files.Summary:
The mode read-only property of the interface returns the access mode passed to 'LockManager.Request' when the lock was requested.
The mode is either "exclusive" (the default) or "shared".

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MIDIAccess
files.Summary: The MIDIAccess interface of the Web MIDI API provides methods for listing MIDI input and output devices, and obtaining access to those devices.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MIDIConnectionEvent
files.Summary: The MIDIConnectionEvent interface of the Web MIDI API is the event passed to the MIDIAccess.Statechange_event event of the interface and the MIDIPort.Statechange_event event of the interface. This occurs any time a new port becomes available, or when a previously available port becomes unavailable. For example, this event is fired whenever a MIDI device is either plugged in to or unplugged from a computer.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MIDIInput
files.Summary: The MIDIInput interface of the Web MIDI API receives messages from a MIDI input port.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MIDIInputMap
files.Summary: The MIDIInputMap read-only interface of the Web MIDI API provides the set of MIDI input ports that are currently available.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MIDIMessageEvent
files.Summary: The MIDIMessageEvent interface of the Web MIDI API represents the event passed to the MIDIInput.Midimessage_event event of the interface. A midimessage event is fired every time a MIDI message is sent from a device represented by a , for example when a MIDI keyboard key is pressed, a knob is tweaked, or a slider is moved.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MIDIOutput
files.Summary: The MIDIOutput interface of the 'Web MIDI API' provides methods to add messages to the queue of an output device, and to clear the queue of messages.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MIDIOutputMap
files.Summary: The MIDIOutputMap read-only interface of the Web MIDI API provides the set of MIDI output ports that are currently available.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MIDIPort
files.Summary: The MIDIPort interface of the 'Web MIDI API' represents a MIDI input or output port.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MIDIPortType
files.Summary: The type read-only property of the interface returns the type of the port, indicating whether this is an input or output MIDI port.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Magnetometer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The Magnetometer interface of the Sensor APIs provides information about the magnetic field as detected by the device's primary magnetometer sensor.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MathMLElement
files.Summary: The MathMLElement interface represents any MathML element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaCapabilities
files.Summary: The MediaCapabilities interface of the Media Capabilities API provides information about the decoding abilities of the device, system and browser. The API can be used to query the browser about the decoding abilities of the device based on codecs, profile, resolution, and bitrates. The information can be used to serve optimal media streams to the user and determine if playback should be smooth and power efficient.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaCapabilitiesDecodingInfo
files.Summary: The decodingInfo() method of the interface returns a promise that fulfils with information about how well the user agent can decode/display media with a given configuration.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaCapabilitiesEncodingInfo
files.Summary:
The encodingInfo() method of the interface returns a promise that fulfills with the tested media configuration's capabilities for encoding media.
This contains the three boolean properties supported, smooth, and powerefficient, which describe how compatible the device is with the type of media.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaDeviceInfo
files.Summary: The MediaDeviceInfo interface of the {{domxref("Media Capture and Streams API", "", "", "nocode")}} contains information that describes a single media input or output device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaDevices
files.Summary: The MediaDevices interface of the {{domxref("Media Capture and Streams API", "", "", "nocode")}} provides access to connected media input devices like cameras and microphones, as well as screen sharing. In essence, it lets you obtain access to any hardware source of media data.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaElementAudioSourceNode
files.Summary: The MediaElementAudioSourceNode interface represents an audio source consisting of an HTML {{ htmlelement("audio") }} or {{ htmlelement("video") }} element. It is an that acts as an audio source.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaEncryptedEvent
files.Summary: The MediaEncryptedEvent interface of the Encrypted Media Extensions API contains the information associated with an HTMLMediaElement/encrypted_event event sent to a when some initialization data is encountered in the media.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaError
files.Summary: The MediaError interface represents an error which occurred while handling media in an HTML media element based on , such as {{HTMLElement("audio")}} or {{HTMLElement("video")}}.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaKeyMessageEvent
files.Summary: The MediaKeyMessageEvent interface of the Encrypted Media Extensions API contains the content and related data when the content decryption module generates a message for the session.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaKeySession
files.Summary: The MediaKeySession interface of the Encrypted Media Extensions API represents a context for message exchange with a content decryption module (CDM).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaKeyStatusMap
files.Summary: The MediaKeyStatusMap interface of the Encrypted Media Extensions API is a read-only map of media key statuses by key IDs.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaKeySystemAccess
files.Summary: The MediaKeySystemAccess interface of the Encrypted Media Extensions API provides access to a Key System for decryption and/or a content protection provider. You can request an instance of this object using the method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaKeys
files.Summary: The MediaKeys interface of Encrypted Media Extensions API represents a set of keys that an associated can use for decryption of media data during playback.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaList
files.Summary: The MediaList interface represents the media queries of a stylesheet, e.g. those set using a link element's media attribute.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaMetadata
files.Summary: The MediaMetadata interface of the {{domxref("Media Session API", "", "", "nocode")}} allows a web page to provide rich media metadata for display in a platform UI.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaQueryList
files.Summary: A MediaQueryList object stores information on a media query applied to a document, with support for both immediate and event-driven matching against the state of the document.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaQueryListEvent
files.Summary: The MediaQueryListEvent object stores information on the changes that have happened to a object instances are available as the event object on a function referenced by a MediaQueryList.Change_event event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaRecorder
files.Summary: The MediaRecorder interface of the MediaStream Recording API provides functionality to easily record media. It is created using the constructor.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaSession
files.Summary: The MediaSession interface of the {{domxref("Media Session API", "", "", "nocode")}} allows a web page to provide custom behaviors for standard media playback interactions, and to report metadata that can be sent by the user agent to the device or operating system for presentation in standardized user interface elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaSessionPlaybackState
files.Summary:
The playbackState property of the
interface indicates whether the current media session is
playing or paused.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaSource
files.Summary: The MediaSource interface of the {{domxref("Media Source Extensions API", "Media Source Extensions API", "", "nocode")}} represents a source of media data for an object. A MediaSource object can be attached to a to be played in the user agent.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaSourceHandle
files.Summary: The MediaSourceHandle interface of the {{domxref("Media Source Extensions API", "Media Source Extensions API", "", "nocode")}} is a proxy for a that can be transferred from a dedicated worker back to the main thread and attached to a media element via its property. MediaSource objects are not transferable because they are event targets, hence the need for MediaSourceHandles.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaStream
files.Summary: The MediaStream interface of the {{domxref("Media Capture and Streams API", "", "", "nocode")}} represents a stream of media content. A stream consists of several tracks, such as video or audio tracks. Each track is specified as an instance of .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaStreamAudioDestinationNode
files.Summary: The MediaStreamAudioDestinationNode interface represents an audio destination consisting of a WebRTC with a single AudioMediaStreamTrack, which can be used in a similar way to a MediaStream obtained from .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaStreamAudioSourceNode
files.Summary: The MediaStreamAudioSourceNode interface is a type of which operates as an audio source whose media is received from a obtained using the WebRTC or Media Capture and Streams APIs.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaStreamTrack
files.Summary: The MediaStreamTrack interface of the {{domxref("Media Capture and Streams API", "", "", "nocode")}} represents a single media track within a stream; typically, these are audio or video tracks, but other track types may exist as well.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaStreamTrackAudioSourceNode
files.Summary: The MediaStreamTrackAudioSourceNode interface is a type of which represents a source of audio data taken from a specific obtained through the WebRTC or Media Capture and Streams APIs.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaStreamTrackEvent
files.Summary: The MediaStreamTrackEvent interface of the {{domxref("Media Capture and Streams API", "", "", "nocode")}} represents events which indicate that a has had tracks added to or removed from the stream through calls to Media Capture and Streams API methods. These events are sent to the stream when these changes occur.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaStreamTrackProcessor
files.Summary: The MediaStreamTrackProcessor interface of the Insertable Streams for MediaStreamTrack API consumes a object's source and generates a stream of media frames.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaTrackConstraints
files.Summary: The MediaTrackConstraints dictionary is used to describe a set of capabilities and the value or values each can take on. A constraints dictionary is passed into to allow a script to establish a set of exact (required) values or ranges and/or preferred values or ranges of values for the track, and the most recently-requested set of custom constraints can be retrieved by calling .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaTrackSettings
files.Summary: The MediaTrackSettings dictionary is used to return the current values configured for each of a 's settings. These values will adhere as closely as possible to any constraints previously described using a object and set using , and will adhere to the default constraints for any properties whose constraints haven't been changed, or whose customized constraints couldn't be matched.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MediaTrackSupportedConstraints
files.Summary: The MediaTrackSupportedConstraints dictionary establishes the list of constrainable properties recognized by the {{Glossary("user agent")}} or browser in its implementation of the object. An object conforming to MediaTrackSupportedConstraints is returned by .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MessageChannel
files.Summary: The MessageChannel interface of the Channel Messaging API allows us to create a new message channel and send data through it via its two properties.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MessageEvent
files.Summary: The MessageEvent interface represents a message received by a target object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MessagePort
files.Summary: The MessagePort interface of the Channel Messaging API represents one of the two ports of a , allowing messages to be sent from one port and listening out for them arriving at the other.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MimeType
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
The MimeType interface provides contains information about a MIME type associated with a particular plugin. Navigator.MimeTypes returns an array of this object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MimeTypeArray
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
The MimeTypeArray interface returns an array of 'MimeType' instances, each of which contains information about a supported browser plugins. This object is returned by the deprecated Navigator.MimeTypes property.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MouseEvent
files.Summary:
The MouseEvent interface represents events that occur due to the user interacting with a pointing device (such as a mouse).
Common events using this interface include Element/click_event, Element/dblclick_event, Element/mouseup_event, Element/mousedown_event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MutationEvent
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
The MutationEvent interface provides event properties that are specific to modifications to the Document Object Model (DOM) hierarchy and nodes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MutationObserver
files.Summary: The MutationObserver interface provides the ability to watch for changes being made to the DOM tree. It is designed as a replacement for the older Mutation Events feature, which was part of the DOM3 Events specification.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.MutationRecord
files.Summary: The MutationRecord is a read-only interface that represents an individual DOM mutation observed by a . It is the object inside the array passed to the callback of a .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NDEFMessage
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NDEFMessage interface of the Web NFC API represents the content of an NDEF message that has been read from or could be written to an NFC tag. An instance is acquired by calling the NDEFMessage() constructor or from the property, which is passed to the NDEFReader.Reading_event event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NDEFReader
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NDEFReader interface of the Web NFC API is used to read from and write data to compatible NFC devices, e.g. NFC tags supporting NDEF, when these devices are within the reader's magnetic induction field.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NDEFReadingEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NDEFReadingEvent interface of the Web NFC API represents events dispatched on new NFC readings obtained by .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NDEFRecord
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NDEFRecord interface of the Web NFC API provides data that can be read from, or written to, compatible NFC devices, e.g. NFC tags supporting NDEF.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NamedNodeMap
files.Summary: The NamedNodeMap interface represents a collection of objects. Objects inside a NamedNodeMap are not in any particular order, unlike , although they may be accessed by an index as in an array.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigateEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NavigateEvent interface of the {{domxref("Navigation API", "Navigation API", "", "nocode")}} is the event object for the Navigation/navigate_event event, which fires when any type of navigation is initiated (this includes usage of {{domxref("History API", "History API", "", "nocode")}} features like ). NavigateEvent provides access to information about that navigation, and allows developers to intercept and control the navigation handling.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Navigation
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The Navigation interface of the {{domxref("Navigation API", "Navigation API", "", "nocode")}} allows control over all navigation actions for the current window in one central place, including initiating navigations programmatically, examining navigation history entries, and managing navigations as they happen.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigationActivation
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NavigationActivation interface of the Navigation API represents a recent cross-document navigation. It contains the navigation type and outgoing and inbound document history entries.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NavigationCurrentEntryChangeEvent interface of the {{domxref("Navigation API", "Navigation API", "", "nocode")}} is the event object for the Navigation/currententrychange_event event, which fires when the has changed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigationDestination
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NavigationDestination interface of the {{domxref("Navigation API", "Navigation API", "", "nocode")}} represents the destination being navigated to in the current navigation.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigationHistoryEntry
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NavigationHistoryEntry interface of the {{domxref("Navigation API", "Navigation API", "", "nocode")}} represents a single navigation history entry.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigationPreloadManager
files.Summary: The NavigationPreloadManager interface of the Service Worker API provides methods for managing the preloading of resources in parallel with service worker bootup.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigationTransition
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NavigationTransition interface of the {{domxref("Navigation API", "Navigation API", "", "nocode")}} represents an ongoing navigation, that is, a navigation that hasn't yet reached the Navigation/navigatesuccess_event or Navigation/navigateerror_event stage.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Navigator
files.Summary: The Navigator interface represents the state and the identity of the user agent. It allows scripts to query it and to register themselves to carry on some activities.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigatorDeviceMemory
files.Summary:
The deviceMemory read-only
property of the interface returns the approximate amount of
device memory in gigabytes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigatorLanguage
files.Summary: The Navigator.language read-only property returns a string representing the preferred language of the user, usually the language of the browser UI.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigatorLocks
files.Summary:
The locks read-only property of
the interface returns a object
which provides methods for requesting a new 'Lock' object and querying
for an existing Lock object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigatorLogin
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NavigatorLogin interface of the Federated Credential Management (FedCM) API defines login functionality for federated identity providers (IdPs). Specifically, it enables a federated identity provider (IdP) to set its login status when a user signs into or out of the IdP.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigatorOnLine
files.Summary:
Returns the online status of the browser. The property returns a boolean value, with
true meaning online and false meaning offline. The property
sends updates whenever the browser's ability to connect to the network changes. The
update occurs when the user follows links or when a script requests a remote page. For
example, the property should return false when users click links soon after
they lose internet connection.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigatorPlugins
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
Returns a object, listing the objects describing the plugins installed in the application.
Named properties of the returned object are not enumerable (except in very old browser versions).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigatorStorage
files.Summary:
The Navigator.storage
read-only property returns the singleton object used to
access the overall storage capabilities of the browser for the current site or app.
The returned object lets you examine and configure persistence of data stores and
learn approximately how much more space your browser has available for local storage
use.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NavigatorUAData
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NavigatorUAData interface of the {{domxref("User-Agent Client Hints API", "", "", "nocode")}} returns information about the browser and operating system of a user.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NetworkInformation
files.Summary:
The NetworkInformation interface of the Network Information API provides information about the connection a device is using to communicate with the network and provides a means for scripts to be notified if the connection type changes.
The NetworkInformation interface cannot be instantiated. It is instead accessed through the connection property of the interface or the interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NetworkInformationSaveData
files.Summary:
The saveData read-only
property of the interface returns true if the user has set a reduced data usage option on the user agent.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Node
files.Summary:
In addition, every kind of DOM node is represented by an interface based on
Node. These include ,
(which , , and
are all based on), and .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NodeIterator
files.Summary: The NodeIterator interface represents an iterator to traverse nodes of a DOM subtree in document order.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NodeList
files.Summary: NodeList objects are collections of nodes, usually returned by properties such as and methods such as Document.QuerySelectorAll.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NonElementParentNode
files.Summary: The Document interface represents any web page loaded in the browser and serves as an entry point into the web page's content, which is the DOM tree.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NotRestoredReasonDetails
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NotRestoredReasonDetails interface of the {{domxref("Performance API", "Performance API", "", "nocode")}} represents a single reason why a navigated page was blocked from using the back/forward cache (bfcache).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NotRestoredReasons
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The NotRestoredReasons interface of the {{domxref("Performance API", "Performance API", "", "nocode")}} provides report data containing reasons why the current document was blocked from using the back/forward cache (bfcache) on navigation.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Notification
files.Summary: The Notification interface of the {{domxref("Notifications API", "", "", "nocode")}} is used to configure and display desktop notifications to the user.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NotificationEvent
files.Summary: The NotificationEvent interface of the {{domxref("Notifications API", "", "", "nocode")}} represents a notification event dispatched on the of a .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.NotificationPermission
files.Summary:
The permission read-only static property of the
interface indicates the current permission granted by the user for the current origin to
display web notifications.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.OTPCredential
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The OTPCredential interface of the 'WebOTP API' is returned when a WebOTP call (i.e. invoked with an otp option) fulfills. It includes a code property that contains the retrieved one-time password (OTP).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.OfflineAudioCompletionEvent
files.Summary: The Web Audio APIOfflineAudioCompletionEvent interface represents events that occur when the processing of an is terminated. The OfflineAudioContext/complete_event event uses this interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.OfflineAudioContext
files.Summary: The OfflineAudioContext interface is an interface representing an audio-processing graph built from linked together s. In contrast with a standard , an OfflineAudioContext doesn't render the audio to the device hardware; instead, it generates it, as fast as it can, and outputs the result to an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.OffscreenCanvas
files.Summary:
The OffscreenCanvas interface provides a canvas that can be rendered off screen, decoupling the DOM and the Canvas API so that the canvas element is no longer entirely dependent on the DOM.
Rendering operations can also be run inside a worker context, allowing you to run some tasks in a separate thread and avoid heavy work on the main thread.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.OffscreenCanvasRenderingContext2D
files.Summary:
The OffscreenCanvasRenderingContext2D interface is a rendering context for drawing to the bitmap of an OffscreenCanvas object.
It is similar to the CanvasRenderingContext2D object, with the following differences:

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.OrientationSensor
files.Summary: The OrientationSensor interface of the Sensor APIs is the base class for orientation sensors. This interface cannot be used directly. Instead it provides properties and methods accessed by interfaces that inherit from it.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.OscillatorNode
files.Summary: The OscillatorNode interface represents a periodic waveform, such as a sine wave. It is an audio-processing module that causes a specified frequency of a given wave to be createdin effect, a constant tone.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.OverconstrainedError
files.Summary: The OverconstrainedError interface of the Media Capture and Streams API indicates that the set of desired capabilities for the current 'MediaStreamTrack' cannot currently be met. When this event is thrown on a MediaStreamTrack, it is muted until either the current constraints can be established or until satisfiable constraints are applied.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PageRevealEvent
files.Summary: The PageRevealEvent event object is made available inside handler functions for the Window.Pagereveal_event event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PageSwapEvent
files.Summary: The PageSwapEvent event object is made available inside handler functions for the Window.Pageswap_event event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PageTransitionEvent
files.Summary: The PageTransitionEvent event object is available inside handler functions for the pageshow and pagehide events, fired when a document is being loaded or unloaded.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PaintWorkletGlobalScope
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PaintWorkletGlobalScope interface of the CSS Painting API represents the global object available inside a paint .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PannerNode
files.Summary: The PannerNode interface defines an audio-processing object that represents the location, direction, and behavior of an audio source signal in a simulated physical space. This uses right-hand Cartesian coordinates to describe the source's position as a vector and its orientation as a 3D directional cone.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ParentNode
files.Summary: Element is the most general base class from which all element objects (i.e. objects that represent elements) in a inherit. It only has methods and properties common to all kinds of elements. More specific classes inherit from Element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PasswordCredential
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PasswordCredential interface of the Credential Management API provides information about a username/password pair. In supporting browsers an instance of this class may be passed in the credential member of the init object for global Window/fetch.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Path2D
files.Summary: The Path2D interface of the Canvas 2D API is used to declare a path that can then be used on a object. The path methods of the CanvasRenderingContext2D interface are also present on this interface, which gives you the convenience of being able to retain and replay your path whenever desired.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PaymentManager
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PaymentManager interface of the {{domxref("Payment Handler API", "Payment Handler API", "", "nocode")}} is used to manage various aspects of payment app functionality.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PaymentMethodChangeEvent
files.Summary: The PaymentMethodChangeEvent interface of the Payment Request API describes the PaymentRequest/paymentmethodchange_event event which is fired by some payment handlers when the user switches payment instruments (e.g., a user selects a "store" card to make a purchase while using Apple Pay).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PaymentRequest
files.Summary: The Payment Request API'sPaymentRequest interface is the primary access point into the API, and lets web content and apps accept payments from the end user on behalf of the operator of the site or the publisher of the app.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PaymentRequestEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PaymentRequestEvent interface of the {{domxref("Payment Handler API", "", "", "nocode")}} is the object passed to a payment handler when a is made.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PaymentRequestUpdateEvent
files.Summary: The PaymentRequestUpdateEvent interface is used for events sent to a instance when changes are made to shipping-related information for a pending . Those events are:

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PaymentResponse
files.Summary: The PaymentResponse interface of the Payment Request API is returned after a user selects a payment method and approves a payment request.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Pbkdf2Params
files.Summary: The Pbkdf2Params dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into , when using the PBKDF2 algorithm.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Performance
files.Summary: The Performance interface provides access to performance-related information for the current page.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceElementTiming
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PerformanceElementTiming interface contains render timing information for image and text node elements the developer annotated with an elementtiming attribute for observation.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceEntry
files.Summary: The PerformanceEntry object encapsulates a single performance metric that is part of the browser's performance timeline.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceEventTiming
files.Summary: The PerformanceEventTiming interface of the Event Timing API provides insights into the latency of certain event types triggered by user interaction.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceLongAnimationFrameTiming
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PerformanceLongAnimationFrameTiming interface is specified in the Long Animation Frames API and provides metrics on long animation frames (LoAFs) that occupy rendering and block other tasks from being executed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceLongTaskTiming
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PerformanceLongTaskTiming interface provides information about tasks that occupy the UI thread for 50 milliseconds or more.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceMark
files.Summary: PerformanceMark is an interface for objects with an of "mark".

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceMeasure
files.Summary: PerformanceMeasure is an abstract interface for objects with an of "measure". Entries of this type are created by calling to add a named (the measure) between two marks to the browser's performance timeline.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceNavigation
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
The legacy PerformanceNavigation interface represents information about how the navigation to the current document was done.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceNavigationTiming
files.Summary: The PerformanceNavigationTiming interface provides methods and properties to store and retrieve metrics regarding the browser's document navigation events. For example, this interface can be used to determine how much time it takes to load or unload a document.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceObserver
files.Summary: The PerformanceObserver interface is used to observe performance measurement events and be notified of new as they are recorded in the browser's performance timeline.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceObserverEntryList
files.Summary: The PerformanceObserverEntryList interface is a list of that were explicitly observed via the method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformancePaintTiming
files.Summary: The PerformancePaintTiming interface provides timing information about "paint" (also called "render") operations during web page construction. "Paint" refers to conversion of the render tree to on-screen pixels.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceResourceTiming
files.Summary: The PerformanceResourceTiming interface enables retrieval and analysis of detailed network timing data regarding the loading of an application's resources. An application can use the timing metrics to determine, for example, the length of time it takes to fetch a specific resource, such as an , {{SVGElement("SVG","SVG element")}}, image, or script.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceScriptTiming
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PerformanceScriptTiming interface is specified in the Long Animation Frames API and provides metrics on individual scripts that contribute to long animation frames (LoAFs).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceServerTiming
files.Summary: The PerformanceServerTiming interface surfaces server metrics that are sent with the response in the Server-Timing HTTP header.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PerformanceTiming
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
WARNING
This interface is deprecated in the Navigation Timing Level 2 specification. Please use the interface instead.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PeriodicSyncEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PeriodicSyncEvent interface of the 'Web Periodic Background Synchronization API' provides a way to run tasks in the service worker with network connectivity.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PeriodicSyncManager
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PeriodicSyncManager interface of the 'Web Periodic Background Synchronization API' provides a way to register tasks to be run in a service worker at periodic intervals with network connectivity. These tasks are referred to as periodic background sync requests. Access PeriodicSyncManager through the 'ServiceWorkerRegistration.PeriodicSync'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PeriodicWave
files.Summary: The PeriodicWave interface defines a periodic waveform that can be used to shape the output of an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PermissionStatus
files.Summary: The PermissionStatus interface of the Permissions API provides the state of an object and an event handler for monitoring changes to said state.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Permissions
files.Summary: The Permissions interface of the Permissions API provides the core Permission API functionality, such as methods for querying and revoking permissions

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PictureInPictureEvent
files.Summary: The PictureInPictureEvent interface represents picture-in-picture-related events, including HTMLVideoElement/enterpictureinpicture_event, HTMLVideoElement/leavepictureinpicture_event and PictureInPictureWindow/resize_event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PictureInPictureWindow
files.Summary: The PictureInPictureWindow interface represents an object able to programmatically obtain the width and height and resize event of the floating video window.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Plugin
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
The Plugin interface provides information about a browser plugin.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PluginArray
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
The PluginArray interface is used to store a list of objects; it's returned by the Navigator.Plugins property. The PluginArray is not a JavaScript array, but has the length property and supports accessing individual items using bracket notation (plugins[2]), as well as via item(index) and namedItem("name") methods.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PointerEvent
files.Summary: The PointerEvent interface represents the state of a DOM event produced by a pointer such as the geometry of the contact point, the device type that generated the event, the amount of pressure that was applied on the contact surface, etc.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PopStateEvent
files.Summary: PopStateEvent is an interface for the Window/popstate_event event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Presentation
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The Presentation can be defined as two possible user agents in the context: Controlling user agent and Receiving user agent.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PresentationAvailability
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
A PresentationAvailability object is associated with available presentation displays and represents the presentation display availability for a presentation request. If the controlling user agent can monitor the list of available presentation displays in the background (without a pending request to start()), the PresentationAvailability object MUST be implemented in a controlling browsing context.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PresentationConnection
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PresentationConnection interface of the Presentation API provides methods and properties for managing a single presentation. Each presentation connection is represented by a PresentationConnection object. Both the controlling user agent and receiving user agentMUST implement PresentationConnection.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PresentationConnectionAvailableEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PresentationConnectionAvailableEvent interface of the Presentation API is fired on a when a connection associated with the object is created.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PresentationConnectionCloseEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PresentationConnectionCloseEvent interface of the Presentation API is fired on a when it is closed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PresentationConnectionList
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
PresentationConnectionList is the collection of incoming presentation connections.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PresentationConnectionState
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The state attribute reflects the presentation connection's current state. Depending on the current PresentationConnectionState, the state attribute can hold one of the following values.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PresentationReceiver
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PresentationReceiver interface of the Presentation API provides a means for a receiving browsing context to access controlling browsing contexts and communicate with them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PresentationRequest
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
A PresentationRequest object is used to initiate or reconnect to a presentation made by a controlling browsing context. The PresentationRequest object MUST be implemented in a controlling browsing context provided by a controlling user agent.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PressureObserver
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PressureObserver interface is part of the Compute Pressure API and is used to observe the pressure changes of system resources such as the CPU.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PressureRecord
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The PressureRecord interface is part of the Compute Pressure API and describes the pressure trend of a source at a specific moment of transition.
