files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ProcessingInstruction
files.Summary: The ProcessingInstruction interface represents a processing instruction; that is, a which embeds an instruction targeting a specific application but that can be ignored by any other applications which don't recognize the instruction.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ProgressEvent
files.Summary: The ProgressEvent interface represents events measuring progress of an underlying process, like an HTTP request (for an XMLHttpRequest, or the loading of the underlying resource of an img, audio, video, style or link).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PromiseRejectionEvent
files.Summary: The PromiseRejectionEvent interface represents events which are sent to the global script context when JavaScript s are rejected. These events are particularly useful for telemetry and debugging purposes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PublicKeyCredential
files.Summary: The PublicKeyCredential interface provides information about a public key / private key pair, which is a credential for logging in to a service using an un-phishable and data-breach resistant asymmetric key pair instead of a password. It inherits from , and is part of the Web Authentication API extension to the Credential Management API.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions
files.Summary: The PublicKeyCredentialCreationOptions dictionary represents the object passed to as the value of the publicKey option: that is, when using create() to create a public key credential using the Web Authentication API.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions
files.Summary: The PublicKeyCredentialRequestOptions dictionary represents the object passed to as the value of the publicKey option:.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PushEvent
files.Summary: The PushEvent interface of the Push API represents a push message that has been received. This event is sent to the global scope of a . It contains the information sent from an application server to a .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PushManager
files.Summary: The PushManager interface of the Push API provides a way to receive notifications from third-party servers as well as request URLs for push notifications.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PushMessageData
files.Summary: The PushMessageData interface of the Push API provides methods which let you retrieve the push data sent by a server in various formats.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PushSubscription
files.Summary:
The PushSubscription interface of the Push API provides a subscription's URL endpoint along with the public key and secrets that should be used for encrypting push messages to this subscription.
This information must be passed to the application server, using any desired application-specific method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.PushSubscriptionOptions
files.Summary: The PushSubscriptionOptions interface of the 'Push API' represents the options associated with a push subscription.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCAudioSourceStats
files.Summary: The RTCAudioSourceStats dictionary of the WebRTC API provides statistics information about an audio track () that is attached to one or more senders ().

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCCertificate
files.Summary: The RTCCertificate interface of the WebRTC API provides an object representing a certificate that an uses to authenticate.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCCertificateStats
files.Summary: The RTCCertificateStats dictionary of the WebRTC API is used to report information about a certificate used by an and its underlying .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCCodecStats
files.Summary: The RTCCodecStats dictionary of the WebRTC API provides statistics about a codec used by {{Glossary("RTP")}} streams that are being sent or received by the associated object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCDTMFSender
files.Summary: The RTCDTMFSender interface provides a mechanism for transmitting DTMF codes on a WebRTC. You gain access to the connection's RTCDTMFSender through the property on the audio track you wish to send DTMF with.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCDTMFToneChangeEvent
files.Summary: The RTCDTMFToneChangeEvent interface represents events sent to indicate that DTMF tones have started or finished playing. This interface is used by the tonechange event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCDataChannel
files.Summary: The RTCDataChannel interface represents a network channel which can be used for bidirectional peer-to-peer transfers of arbitrary data. Every data channel is associated with an , and each peer connection can have up to a theoretical maximum of 65,534 data channels (the actual limit may vary from browser to browser).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCDataChannelEvent
files.Summary:
The RTCDataChannelEvent interface
represents an event related to a specific .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCDataChannelStats
files.Summary: The RTCDataChannelStats dictionary of the WebRTC API provides statistics related to one object on the connection.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCDtlsTransport
files.Summary: The RTCDtlsTransport interface provides access to information about the Datagram Transport Layer Security (DTLS) transport over which a 's {{Glossary("RTP")}} and {{Glossary("RTCP")}} packets are sent and received by its and objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCDtlsTransportState
files.Summary:
The state read-only property of the
interface provides information which describes a
Datagram Transport Layer Security (DTLS) transport state.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCEncodedAudioFrame
files.Summary: The RTCEncodedAudioFrame of the WebRTC API represents an encoded audio frame in the WebRTC receiver or sender pipeline, which may be modified using a WebRTC Encoded Transform.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCEncodedVideoFrame
files.Summary: The RTCEncodedVideoFrame of the WebRTC API represents an encoded video frame in the WebRTC receiver or sender pipeline, which may be modified using a WebRTC Encoded Transform.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCEncodedVideoFrameType
files.Summary: The type read-only property of the interface indicates whether this frame is a key frame, delta frame, or empty frame.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCError
files.Summary: The RTCError interface describes an error which has occurred while handling WebRTC operations. It's based upon the standard interface that describes general DOM errors.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCErrorEvent
files.Summary: The WebRTC API's RTCErrorEvent interface represents an error sent to a WebRTC object. It's based on the standard interface, but adds RTC-specific information describing the error, as shown below.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCIceCandidate
files.Summary: The RTCIceCandidate interfacepart of the WebRTC APIrepresents a candidate Interactive Connectivity Establishment ({{Glossary("ICE")}}) configuration which may be used to establish an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCIceCandidatePair
files.Summary: The RTCIceCandidatePair dictionary describes a pair of ICE candidates which together comprise a description of a viable connection between two WebRTC endpoints. It is used as the return value from to identify the currently-selected candidate pair identified by the ICE agent.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCIceCandidatePairStats
files.Summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats dictionary of the WebRTC API is used to report statistics that provide insight into the quality and performance of an while connected and configured as described by the specified pair of {{Glossary("ICE")}} candidates.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCIceCandidateStats
files.Summary: The RTCIceCandidateStats dictionary of the WebRTC API is used to report statistics related to an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCIceCandidateType
files.Summary: The interface's read-only type specifies the type of candidate the object represents.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCIceParameters
files.Summary: The RTCIceParameters dictionary specifies the username fragment and password assigned to an ICE session.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCIceTransport
files.Summary:
The RTCIceTransport interface provides access to information about the ICE transport layer over which the data is being sent and received.
This is particularly useful if you need to access state information about the connection.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCIceTransportState
files.Summary: The state read-only property of the interface returns the current state of the ICE transport, so you can determine the state of ICE gathering in which the ICE agent currently is operating.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCIdentityAssertion
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The RTCIdentityAssertion interface of the WebRTC API represents the identity of a remote peer of the current connection. If no peer has yet been set and verified, then this interface returns null. Once set it can't be changed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCInboundRtpStreamStats
files.Summary: The RTCInboundRtpStreamStats dictionary of the WebRTC API is used to report statistics related to the receiving end of an RTP stream on the local end of the .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCOutboundRtpStreamStats
files.Summary: The RTCOutboundRtpStreamStats dictionary of the WebRTC API is used to report metrics and statistics related to an outbound {{Glossary("RTP")}} stream being sent by an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCPeerConnection
files.Summary:
The RTCPeerConnection interface represents a WebRTC connection between the local computer and a remote peer.
It provides methods to connect to a remote peer, maintain and monitor the connection, and close the connection once it's no longer needed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCPeerConnectionIceErrorEvent
files.Summary: The RTCPeerConnectionIceErrorEvent interfacebased upon the interfaceprovides details pertaining to an {{Glossary("ICE")}} error announced by sending an RTCPeerConnection.Icecandidateerror_event event to the object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCPeerConnectionIceEvent
files.Summary: The RTCPeerConnectionIceEvent interface represents events that occur in relation to {{Glossary("ICE")}} candidates with the target, usually an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCPeerConnectionStats
files.Summary: The RTCPeerConnectionStats dictionary of the WebRTC API provides information about the high level peer connection ().

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCRemoteInboundRtpStreamStats
files.Summary:
The RTCRemoteInboundRtpStreamStats dictionary of the WebRTC API is used to report statistics from the remote endpoint about a particular incoming RTP stream.
These will correspond to an outgoing RTP stream at the local end of the .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats
files.Summary:
The RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats dictionary of the WebRTC API is used to report statistics from a remote endpoint about its outbound RTP stream.
This will correspond to an inbound stream that is currently being received by the local object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCRtpReceiver
files.Summary: The RTCRtpReceiver interface of the WebRTC API manages the reception and decoding of data for a on an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCRtpScriptTransform
files.Summary: The RTCRtpScriptTransform interface of the WebRTC API is used to insert a WebRTC Encoded Transform (a running in a worker thread) into the WebRTC sender and receiver pipelines.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCRtpScriptTransformer
files.Summary: The RTCRtpScriptTransformer interface of the WebRTC API provides a worker-side Stream API interface that a WebRTC Encoded Transform can use to modify encoded media frames in the incoming and outgoing WebRTC pipelines.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCRtpSender
files.Summary: The RTCRtpSender interface provides the ability to control and obtain details about how a particular is encoded and sent to a remote peer.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCRtpTransceiver
files.Summary: The WebRTC interface RTCRtpTransceiver describes a permanent pairing of an and an , along with some shared state.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCRtpTransceiverDirection
files.Summary: The property direction is a string that indicates the transceiver's preferred directionality.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCSctpTransport
files.Summary: The RTCSctpTransport interface provides information which describes a Stream Control Transmission Protocol (SCTP) transport. This provides information about limitations of the transport, but also provides a way to access the underlying Datagram Transport Layer Security (DTLS) transport over which SCTP packets for all of an 's data channels are sent and received.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCSctpTransportState
files.Summary: The state read-only property of the interface provides information which describes a Stream Control Transmission Protocol ({{Glossary("SCTP")}}) transport state.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCSessionDescription
files.Summary: The RTCSessionDescription interface describes one end of a connectionor potential connectionand how it's configured. Each RTCSessionDescription consists of a description indicating which part of the offer/answer negotiation process it describes and of the {{Glossary("SDP")}} descriptor of the session.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCStatsReport
files.Summary: The RTCStatsReport interface of the WebRTC API provides a statistics report for a , , or .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCTrackEvent
files.Summary: The WebRTC API interface RTCTrackEvent represents the RTCPeerConnection.Track_event event, which is sent when a new is added to an which is part of the .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCTransformEvent
files.Summary: The RTCTransformEvent of the WebRTC API represent an event that is fired in a dedicated worker when an encoded frame has been queued for processing by a WebRTC Encoded Transform.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCTransportStats
files.Summary: The RTCTransportStats dictionary of the WebRTC API provides information about the transport ( and its underlying ) used by a particular candidate pair.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RTCVideoSourceStats
files.Summary: The RTCVideoSourceStats dictionary of the WebRTC API provides statistics information about a video track () that is attached to one or more senders ().

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RadioNodeList
files.Summary: The RadioNodeList interface represents a collection of elements in a {{HTMLElement("form")}} returned by a call to HTMLFormControlsCollection.NamedItem.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Range
files.Summary: The Range interface represents a fragment of a document that can contain nodes and parts of text nodes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ReadableByteStreamController
files.Summary:
The ReadableByteStreamController interface of the Streams API represents a controller for a readable byte stream.
It allows control of the state and internal queue of a with an underlying byte source, and enables efficient zero-copy transfer of data from the underlying source to a consumer when the stream's internal queue is empty.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ReadableStream
files.Summary: The ReadableStream interface of the Streams API represents a readable stream of byte data. The Fetch API offers a concrete instance of a ReadableStream through the Response.Body property of a object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ReadableStreamBYOBReader
files.Summary:
The ReadableStreamBYOBReader interface of the Streams API defines a reader for a that supports zero-copy reading from an underlying byte source.
It is used for efficient copying from underlying sources where the data is delivered as an "anonymous" sequence of bytes, such as files.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ReadableStreamBYOBRequest
files.Summary: The ReadableStreamBYOBRequest interface of the Streams API represents a "pull request" for data from an underlying source that will made as a zero-copy transfer to a consumer (bypassing the stream's internal queues).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ReadableStreamDefaultController
files.Summary: The ReadableStreamDefaultController interface of the Streams API represents a controller allowing control of a 's state and internal queue. Default controllers are for streams that are not byte streams.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ReadableStreamDefaultReader
files.Summary: The ReadableStreamDefaultReader interface of the Streams API represents a default reader that can be used to read stream data supplied from a network (such as a fetch request).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RelativeOrientationSensor
files.Summary: The RelativeOrientationSensor interface of the Sensor APIs describes the device's physical orientation without regard to the Earth's reference coordinate system.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RemotePlayback
files.Summary: The RemotePlayback interface of the 'Remote Playback API' allows the page to detect availability of remote playback devices, then connect to and control playing on these devices.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RemotePlaybackState
files.Summary: The state read-only property of the interface returns the current state of the RemotePlayback connection.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Report
files.Summary: The Report interface of the Reporting API represents a single report.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ReportBody
files.Summary: The ReportBody interface of the 'Reporting API' represents the body of a report. Individual report types inherit from this interface, adding specific attributes relevant to the particular report.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ReportingObserver
files.Summary: The ReportingObserver interface of the Reporting API allows you to collect and access reports.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Request
files.Summary: The Request interface of the Fetch API represents a resource request.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RequestCache
files.Summary: The cache read-only property of the interface contains the cache mode of the request. It controls how the request will interact with the browser's HTTP cache.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RequestCredentials
files.Summary: The credentials read-only property of the interface reflects the value given to the constructor in the credentials option. It determines whether or not the browser sends credentials with the request, as well as whether any Set-Cookie response headers are respected.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RequestDestination
files.Summary:
The destination read-only
property of the interface returns a string
describing the type of content being requested.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RequestInit
files.Summary: The RequestInit dictionary of the Fetch API represents the set of options that can be used to configure a fetch request.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RequestMode
files.Summary:
The mode read-only property of the
interface contains the mode of the request (e.g., cors,
no-cors, same-origin, or navigate.) This is used
to determine if cross-origin requests lead to valid responses, and which properties of the response are readable.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RequestRedirect
files.Summary: The redirect read-only property of the interface contains the mode for how redirects are handled.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ResizeObserver
files.Summary: The ResizeObserver interface reports changes to the dimensions of an 'Element''s content or border box, or the bounding box of an 'SVGElement'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ResizeObserverEntry
files.Summary: The ResizeObserverEntry interface represents the object passed to the 'ResizeObserver.ResizeObserver' constructor's callback function, which allows you to access the new dimensions of the or being observed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ResizeObserverSize
files.Summary: The ResizeObserverSize interface of the Resize Observer API is used by the interface to access the box sizing properties of the element being observed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Response
files.Summary: The Response interface of the Fetch API represents the response to a request.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ResponseType
files.Summary:
The type read-only property of the interface contains the type of the response.
It can be one of the following:

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RsaHashedImportParams
files.Summary: The RsaHashedImportParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into or , when importing any RSA-based key pair: that is, when the algorithm is identified as any of RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5, RSA-PSS, or RSA-OAEP.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RsaHashedKeyGenParams
files.Summary: The RsaHashedKeyGenParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into , when generating any RSA-based key pair: that is, when the algorithm is identified as any of RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5, RSA-PSS, or RSA-OAEP.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RsaOaepParams
files.Summary: The RsaOaepParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into , , , or , when using the RSA_OAEP algorithm.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.RsaPssParams
files.Summary: The RsaPssParams dictionary of the Web Crypto API represents the object that should be passed as the algorithm parameter into or , when using the RSA-PSS algorithm.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGAElement
files.Summary: The SVGAElement interface provides access to the properties of an a element, as well as methods to manipulate them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGAngle
files.Summary: The SVGAngle interface is used to represent a value that can be an {{cssxref("<angle>")}} or {{cssxref("<number>")}} value.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGAnimateElement
files.Summary: The SVGAnimateElement interface corresponds to the animate element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGAnimateMotionElement
files.Summary: The SVGAnimateMotionElement interface corresponds to the animateMotion element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGAnimateTransformElement
files.Summary: The SVGAnimateTransformElement interface corresponds to the animateTransform element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGAnimatedEnumeration
files.Summary: The SVGAnimatedEnumeration interface describes attribute values which are constants from a particular enumeration and which can be animated.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGAnimatedLength
files.Summary: The SVGAnimatedLength interface represents attributes of type <length> which can be animated.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGAnimatedRect
files.Summary: The SVGAnimatedRect interface is used for attributes of basic SVGRect which can be animated.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGAnimatedString
files.Summary: The SVGAnimatedString interface represents string attributes which can be animated from each SVG declaration. You need to create SVG attribute before doing anything else, everything should be declared inside this.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGAnimationElement
files.Summary: The SVGAnimationElement interface is the base interface for all of the animation element interfaces: , , SVGAnimateColorElement, and .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGCircleElement
files.Summary: The SVGCircleElement interface is an interface for the circle element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGClipPathElement
files.Summary: The SVGClipPathElement interface provides access to the properties of clipPath elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGComponentTransferFunctionElement
files.Summary: The SVGComponentTransferFunctionElement interface defines a base interface used by the component transfer function interfaces.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGDefsElement
files.Summary: The SVGDefsElement interface corresponds to the defs element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGDescElement
files.Summary: The SVGDescElement interface corresponds to the desc element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGElement
files.Summary: All of the SVG DOM interfaces that correspond directly to elements in the SVG language derive from the SVGElement interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGEllipseElement
files.Summary: The SVGEllipseElement interface provides access to the properties of ellipse elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEBlendElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEBlendElement interface corresponds to the feBlend element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEColorMatrixElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEColorMatrixElement interface corresponds to the feColorMatrix element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEComponentTransferElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEComponentTransferElement interface corresponds to the feComponentTransfer element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFECompositeElement
files.Summary: The SVGFECompositeElement interface corresponds to the feComposite element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEConvolveMatrixElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEConvolveMatrixElement interface corresponds to the feConvolveMatrix element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEDiffuseLightingElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEDiffuseLightingElement interface corresponds to the feDiffuseLighting element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEDisplacementMapElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEDisplacementMapElement interface corresponds to the feDisplacementMap element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEDistantLightElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEDistantLightElement interface corresponds to the feDistantLight element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEDropShadowElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEDropShadowElement interface corresponds to the feDropShadow element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEFloodElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEFloodElement interface corresponds to the feFlood element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEGaussianBlurElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEGaussianBlurElement interface corresponds to the feGaussianBlur element.

files.Summary: The SVGFEImageElement interface corresponds to the feImage element.

files.Summary: The SVGFEMergeElement interface corresponds to the feMerge element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEMergeNodeElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEMergeNodeElement interface corresponds to the feMergeNode element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEMorphologyElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEMorphologyElement interface corresponds to the feMorphology element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFEOffsetElement
files.Summary: The SVGFEOffsetElement interface corresponds to the feOffset element.

files.Summary: The SVGFEPointLightElement interface corresponds to the fePointLight element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGFESpecularLightingElement
files.Summary: The SVGFESpecularLightingElement interface corresponds to the feSpecularLighting element.

files.Summary: The SVGFESpotLightElement interface corresponds to the feSpotLight element.

files.Summary: The SVGFETileElement interface corresponds to the feTile element.

files.Summary: The SVGFETurbulenceElement interface corresponds to the feTurbulence element.

files.Summary: The SVGFilterElement interface provides access to the properties of filter elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGForeignObjectElement
files.Summary: The SVGForeignObjectElement interface provides access to the properties of foreignObject elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGGElement
files.Summary: The SVGGElement interface corresponds to the g element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGGeometryElement
files.Summary: The SVGGeometryElement interface represents SVG elements whose rendering is defined by geometry with an equivalent path, and which can be filled and stroked. This includes paths and the basic shapes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGGradientElement
files.Summary: The SVGGradient interface is a base interface used by and .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGGraphicsElement
files.Summary: The SVGGraphicsElement interface represents SVG elements whose primary purpose is to directly render graphics into a group.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGImageElement
files.Summary: The SVGImageElement interface corresponds to the image element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGLengthList
files.Summary: The SVGLengthList interface defines a list of objects. It is used for the and properties of .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGLineElement
files.Summary: The SVGLineElement interface provides access to the properties of line elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGLinearGradientElement
files.Summary: The SVGLinearGradientElement interface corresponds to the linearGradient element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGMPathElement
files.Summary: The SVGMPathElement interface corresponds to the mpath element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGMarkerElement
files.Summary: The SVGMarkerElement interface provides access to the properties of marker elements, as well as methods to manipulate them. The marker element defines the graphics used for drawing marks on a shape.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGMaskElement
files.Summary: The SVGMaskElement interface provides access to the properties of mask elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGMetadataElement
files.Summary: The SVGMetadataElement interface corresponds to the metadata element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGNumber
files.Summary: The SVGNumber interface corresponds to the {{cssxref("<number>")}} basic data type.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGPathElement
files.Summary: The SVGPathElement interface corresponds to the path element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGPatternElement
files.Summary: The SVGPatternElement interface corresponds to the pattern element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGPointList
files.Summary: The SVGPointList interface represents a list of SVGPoint objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGPolygonElement
files.Summary: The SVGPolygonElement interface provides access to the properties of polygon elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGPolylineElement
files.Summary: The SVGPolylineElement interface provides access to the properties of polyline elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGRadialGradientElement
files.Summary: The SVGRadialGradientElement interface corresponds to the RadialGradient element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGRectElement
files.Summary: The SVGRectElement interface provides access to the properties of rect elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGSVGElement
files.Summary: The SVGSVGElement interface provides access to the properties of svg elements, as well as methods to manipulate them. This interface contains also various miscellaneous commonly-used utility methods, such as matrix operations and the ability to control the time of redraw on visual rendering devices.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGScriptElement
files.Summary: The SVGScriptElement interface corresponds to the SVG script element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGSetElement
files.Summary: The SVGSetElement interface corresponds to the set element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGStopElement
files.Summary: The SVGStopElement interface corresponds to the stop element.

files.Summary: The SVGSwitchElement interface corresponds to the switch element.

files.Summary: The SVGSymbolElement interface corresponds to the symbol element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGTSpanElement
files.Summary: The SVGTSpanElement interface represents a tspan element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGTextContentElement
files.Summary: The SVGTextContentElement interface is implemented by elements that support rendering child text content. It is inherited by various text-related interfaces, such as , , SVGTRefElement, and .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGTextElement
files.Summary: The SVGTextElement interface corresponds to the text elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGTextPathElement
files.Summary: The SVGTextPathElement interface corresponds to the textPath element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGTextPositioningElement
files.Summary: The SVGTextPositioningElement interface is implemented by elements that support attributes that position individual text glyphs. It is inherited by , , and SVGTRefElement.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGTitleElement
files.Summary: The SVGTitleElement interface corresponds to the title element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGUnitTypes
files.Summary: The SVGUnitTypes interface defines a commonly used set of constants used for reflecting gradientUnits, patternContentUnits and other similar attributes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SVGViewElement
files.Summary: The SVGViewElement interface provides access to the properties of view elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Scheduler
files.Summary: The Scheduler interface of the Prioritized Task Scheduling API provides methods for scheduling prioritized tasks.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Scheduling
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The Scheduling object provides methods and properties to control scheduling tasks within the current document.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Screen
files.Summary: The Screen interface represents a screen, usually the one on which the current window is being rendered, and is obtained using .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ScreenDetailed
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The ScreenDetailed interface of the Window Management API represents detailed information about one specific screen available to the user's device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ScreenDetails
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The ScreenDetails interface of the Window Management API represents the details of all the screens available to the user's device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ScreenOrientation
files.Summary: The ScreenOrientation interface of the Screen Orientation API provides information about the current orientation of the document.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ScriptProcessorNode
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
The ScriptProcessorNode interface allows the generation, processing, or analyzing of audio using JavaScript.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ScrollTimeline
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The ScrollTimeline interface of the {{domxref("Web Animations API", "Web Animations API", "", "nocode")}} represents a scroll progress timeline (see CSS scroll-driven animations for more details).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SecurePaymentConfirmationRequest
files.Summary: The SecurePaymentConfirmationRequest dictionary describes input to the Payment Request API when used to authenticate a user during an e-commerce transaction using SPC with Payment Request API.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SecurityPolicyViolationEvent
files.Summary: The SecurityPolicyViolationEvent interface inherits from , and represents the event object of a securitypolicyviolation event sent on an Element/securitypolicyviolation_event, Document/securitypolicyviolation_event, or {{domxref("WorkerGlobalScope/securitypolicyviolation_event", "worker","","nocode")}} when its Content Security Policy (CSP) is violated.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SecurityPolicyViolationEventDisposition
files.Summary: The disposition read-only property of the interface indicates how the violated Content Security Policy (CSP) is configured to be treated by the user agent.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Selection
files.Summary: A Selection object represents the range of text selected by the user or the current position of the caret. Each is associated with a unique selection object, which can be retrieved by or and then be examined and modified.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Sensor
files.Summary: The Sensor interface of the Sensor APIs is the base class for all the other sensor interfaces. This interface cannot be used directly. Instead it provides properties, event handlers, and methods accessed by interfaces that inherit from it.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SensorErrorEvent
files.Summary: The SensorErrorEvent interface of the Sensor APIs provides information about errors thrown by a 'Sensor' or derived interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Serial
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The Serial interface of the Web Serial API provides attributes and methods for finding and connecting to serial ports from a web page.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SerialPort
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The SerialPort interface of the Web Serial API provides access to a serial port on the host device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ServiceWorker
files.Summary: The ServiceWorker interface of the Service Worker API provides a reference to a service worker. Multiple browsing context (e.g. pages, workers, etc.) can be associated with the same service worker, each through a unique ServiceWorker object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ServiceWorkerContainer
files.Summary: The ServiceWorkerContainer interface of the Service Worker API provides an object representing the service worker as an overall unit in the network ecosystem, including facilities to register, unregister and update service workers, and access the state of service workers and their registrations.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ServiceWorkerGlobalScope
files.Summary: The ServiceWorkerGlobalScope interface of the Service Worker API represents the global execution context of a service worker.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ServiceWorkerRegistration
files.Summary: The ServiceWorkerRegistration interface of the Service Worker API represents the service worker registration. You register a service worker to control one or more pages that share the same origin.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ServiceWorkerState
files.Summary:
The state read-only property of the
interface returns a string representing the current state
of the service worker. It can be one of the following values: parsed, installing,
installed, activating, activated, or
redundant.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ShadowRoot
files.Summary: The ShadowRoot interface of the Shadow DOM API is the root node of a DOM subtree that is rendered separately from a document's main DOM tree.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ShadowRootMode
files.Summary:
The mode read-only property of the specifies its mode either open or closed.
This defines whether or not the shadow root's internal features are accessible from JavaScript.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SharedStorage
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The SharedStorage interface of the {{domxref("Shared Storage API", "Shared Storage API", "", "nocode")}} represents the shared storage for a particular origin, defining methods to write data to the shared storage.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SharedStorageWorklet
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The SharedStorageWorklet interface of the {{domxref("Shared Storage API", "Shared Storage API", "", "nocode")}} represents the shared storage worklet for the current origin.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SharedStorageWorkletGlobalScope
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The SharedStorageWorkletGlobalScope interface of the {{domxref("Shared Storage API", "Shared Storage API", "", "nocode")}} represents the global scope of a module.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SharedWorker
files.Summary: The SharedWorker interface represents a specific kind of worker that can be accessed from several browsing contexts, such as several windows, iframes or even workers. They implement an interface different than dedicated workers and have a different global scope, .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SharedWorkerGlobalScope
files.Summary: The SharedWorkerGlobalScope object (the global scope) is accessible through the keyword. Some additional global functions, namespaces objects, and constructors, not typically associated with the worker global scope, but available on it, are listed in the JavaScript Reference. See the complete list of functions available to workers.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SnapEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The SnapEvent interface defines the event object for the Element/scrollsnapchanging_event and Element/scrollsnapchange_event events. Respectively, these fire on on a scroll container when the browser determines that a new scroll snap target is pending (will be selected when the current scroll gesture ends), and when a new snap target is selected.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SourceBuffer
files.Summary: The SourceBuffer interface represents a chunk of media to be passed into an and played, via a object. This can be made up of one or several media segments.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SourceBufferList
files.Summary: The SourceBufferList interface represents a simple container list for multiple objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechGrammar
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The SpeechGrammar interface of the Web Speech API represents a set of words or patterns of words that we want the recognition service to recognize.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechGrammarList
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The SpeechGrammarList interface of the Web Speech API represents a list of objects containing words or patterns of words that we want the recognition service to recognize.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechRecognition
files.Summary: The SpeechRecognition interface of the Web Speech API is the controller interface for the recognition service; this also handles the sent from the recognition service.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechRecognitionAlternative
files.Summary: The SpeechRecognitionAlternative interface of the Web Speech API represents a single word that has been recognized by the speech recognition service.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechRecognitionErrorEvent
files.Summary: The SpeechRecognitionErrorEvent interface of the Web Speech API represents error messages from the recognition service.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechRecognitionEvent
files.Summary: The SpeechRecognitionEvent interface of the Web Speech API represents the event object for the SpeechRecognition.Result_event and SpeechRecognition.Nomatch_event events, and contains all the data associated with an interim or final speech recognition result.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechRecognitionResult
files.Summary: The SpeechRecognitionResult interface of the Web Speech API represents a single recognition match, which may contain multiple objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechRecognitionResultList
files.Summary: The SpeechRecognitionResultList interface of the Web Speech API represents a list of objects, or a single one if results are being captured in mode.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechSynthesis
files.Summary: The SpeechSynthesis interface of the Web Speech API is the controller interface for the speech service; this can be used to retrieve information about the synthesis voices available on the device, start and pause speech, and other commands besides.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechSynthesisErrorEvent
files.Summary: The SpeechSynthesisErrorEvent interface of the Web Speech API contains information about any errors that occur while processing objects in the speech service.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechSynthesisEvent
files.Summary: The SpeechSynthesisEvent interface of the Web Speech API contains information about the current state of objects that have been processed in the speech service.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechSynthesisUtterance
files.Summary:
The SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface of the Web Speech API represents a speech request.
It contains the content the speech service should read and information about how to read it (e.g. language, pitch and volume.)

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SpeechSynthesisVoice
files.Summary:
The SpeechSynthesisVoice interface of the Web Speech API represents a voice that the system supports.
Every SpeechSynthesisVoice has its own relative speech service including information about language, name and URI.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.StaticRange
files.Summary: The DOMStaticRange interface extends to provide a method to specify a range of content in the DOM whose contents don't update to reflect changes which occur within the DOM tree.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.StereoPannerNode
files.Summary: The StereoPannerNode interface of the Web Audio API represents a simple stereo panner node that can be used to pan an audio stream left or right. It is an audio-processing module that positions an incoming audio stream in a stereo image using a low-cost equal-power panning algorithm.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Storage
files.Summary: The Storage interface of the Web Storage API provides access to a particular domain's session or local storage. It allows, for example, the addition, modification, or deletion of stored data items.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.StorageAccessHandle
files.Summary: The StorageAccessHandle interface represents access to unpartitioned state granted by a call to .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.StorageEvent
files.Summary:
The StorageEvent interface is implemented by the Window/storage_event event, which is
sent to a window
when a storage area the window has access to is changed within the context of another document.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.StorageManager
files.Summary: The StorageManager interface of the Storage API provides an interface for managing persistence permissions and estimating available storage. You can get a reference to this interface using either Navigator.Storage or WorkerNavigator.Storage.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.StylePropertyMap
files.Summary: The StylePropertyMap interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API provides a representation of a CSS declaration block that is an alternative to .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.StylePropertyMapReadOnly
files.Summary: The StylePropertyMapReadOnly interface of the CSS Typed Object Model API provides a read-only representation of a CSS declaration block that is an alternative to . Retrieve an instance of this interface using 'Element.ComputedStyleMap'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.StyleSheet
files.Summary: An object implementing the StyleSheet interface represents a single style sheet. CSS style sheets will further implement the more specialized interface.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.StyleSheetList
files.Summary: The StyleSheetList interface represents a list of objects. An instance of this object can be returned by Document.StyleSheets.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SubmitEvent
files.Summary: The SubmitEvent interface defines the object used to represent an {{Glossary("HTML")}} form's HTMLFormElement.Submit_event event. This event is fired at the {{HTMLElement("form")}} when the form's submit action is invoked.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SubtleCrypto
files.Summary: The SubtleCrypto interface of the Web Crypto API provides a number of low-level cryptographic functions.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SyncEvent
files.Summary: The SyncEvent interface of the {{domxref("Background Synchronization API", "", "", "nocode")}} represents a sync action that is dispatched on the of a ServiceWorker.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.SyncManager
files.Summary: The SyncManager interface of the {{domxref("Background Synchronization API", "", "", "nocode")}} provides an interface for registering and listing sync registrations.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TaskAttributionTiming
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The TaskAttributionTiming interface returns information about the work involved in a long task and its associate frame context. The frame context, also called the container, is the iframe, embed or object that is being implicated, on the whole, for a long task.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TaskController
files.Summary:
The TaskController interface of the Prioritized Task Scheduling API represents a controller object that can be used to both abort and change the priority of one or more prioritized tasks.
If there is no need to change task priorities, then can be used instead.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TaskPriorityChangeEvent
files.Summary: The TaskPriorityChangeEvent is the interface for the prioritychange event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TaskSignal
files.Summary: The TaskSignal interface of the Prioritized Task Scheduling API represents a signal object that allows you to communicate with a prioritized task, and abort it or change the priority (if required) via a 'TaskController' object.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Text
files.Summary: The Text interface represents a text in a DOM tree.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextDecoder
files.Summary: The TextDecoder interface represents a decoder for a specific text encoding, such as UTF-8, ISO-8859-2, KOI8-R, GBK, etc. A decoder takes a stream of bytes as input and emits a stream of code points.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextDecoderStream
files.Summary:
The TextDecoderStream interface of the 'Encoding API' converts a stream of text in a binary encoding, such as UTF-8 etc., to a stream of strings.
It is the streaming equivalent of .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextEncoder
files.Summary: The TextEncoder interface takes a stream of code points as input and emits a stream of UTF-8 bytes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextEncoderStream
files.Summary: The TextEncoderStream interface of the 'Encoding API' converts a stream of strings into bytes in the UTF-8 encoding. It is the streaming equivalent of .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextEvent
files.Summary:
IMPORTANT
Deprecated
The TextEvent interface is a legacy UI event interface for reporting changes to text UI elements.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextFormat
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The TextFormat interface represents specific formatting that should be applied to a range of text in an editable text region that's attached to an instance. The text formatting is requested by the {{glossary("Input Method Editor")}} (IME) window that the user is composing text with.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextFormatUpdateEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The TextFormatUpdateEvent interface is a DOM event that represents a list of text formats that an {{glossary("Input Method Editor")}} (IME) window wants to apply to the text being composed in an editable region that's attached to an instance.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextMetrics
files.Summary: The TextMetrics interface represents the dimensions of a piece of text in the canvas; a TextMetrics instance can be retrieved using the CanvasRenderingContext2D.MeasureText method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextTrack
files.Summary: The TextTrack interface of the WebVTT API represents a text track associated with a media element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextTrackCue
files.Summary: The TextTrackCue interface of the WebVTT API is the abstract base class for the various derived cue types, such as ; you will work with these derived types rather than the base class.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextTrackCueList
files.Summary: The TextTrackCueList interface of the WebVTT API is an array-like object that represents a dynamically updating list of objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextTrackKind
files.Summary: The kind read-only property of the interface returns the kind of text track this object represents. This decides how the track will be handled by a user agent.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextTrackList
files.Summary: The TextTrackList interface is used to represent a list of the text tracks defined for the associated video or audio element, with each track represented by a separate object in the list.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextTrackMode
files.Summary:
The interface's
mode property is a string specifying and controlling the
text track's mode: disabled, hidden, or
showing. You can read this value to determine the current mode,
and you can change this value to switch modes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TextUpdateEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The TextUpdateEvent interface is a DOM event that represents a text or selection update in an editable text region that's attached to an instance.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TimeEvent
files.Summary: The TimeEvent interface, a part of SVG SMIL animation, provides specific contextual information associated with Time events.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TimeRanges
files.Summary: A TimeRanges object includes one or more ranges of time, each specified by a starting time offset and an ending time offset. You reference each time range by using the start() and end() methods, passing the index number of the time range you want to retrieve.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ToggleEvent
files.Summary: The ToggleEvent interface represents an event notifying the user an Element's state has changed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Touch
files.Summary: The Touch interface represents a single contact point on a touch-sensitive device. The contact point is commonly a finger or stylus and the device may be a touchscreen or trackpad.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TouchEvent
files.Summary: The TouchEvent interface represents an which is sent when the state of contacts with a touch-sensitive surface changes. This surface can be a touch screen or trackpad, for example. The event can describe one or more points of contact with the screen and includes support for detecting movement, addition and removal of contact points, and so forth.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TouchList
files.Summary: The TouchList interface represents a list of contact points on a touch surface. For example, if the user has three fingers on the touch surface (such as a screen or trackpad), the corresponding TouchList object would have one object for each finger, for a total of three entries.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TrackEvent
files.Summary: The TrackEvent interface of the HTML DOM API is used for events which represent changes to a set of available tracks on an HTML media element; these events are addtrack and removetrack.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TransformStream
files.Summary: The TransformStream interface of the Streams API represents a concrete implementation of the pipe chaintransform stream concept.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TransformStreamDefaultController
files.Summary: The TransformStreamDefaultController interface of the Streams API provides methods to manipulate the associated and .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TransitionEvent
files.Summary: The TransitionEvent interface represents events providing information related to transitions.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TreeWalker
files.Summary: The TreeWalker object represents the nodes of a document subtree and a position within them.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TrustedHTML
files.Summary: The TrustedHTML interface of the {{domxref("Trusted Types API", "", "", "nocode")}} represents a string that a developer can insert into an injection sink that will render it as HTML. These objects are created via and therefore have no constructor.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TrustedScript
files.Summary: The TrustedScript interface of the {{domxref("Trusted Types API", "", "", "nocode")}} represents a string with an uncompiled script body that a developer can insert into an injection sink that might execute the script. These objects are created via and therefore have no constructor.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TrustedScriptURL
files.Summary: The TrustedScriptURL interface of the {{domxref("Trusted Types API", "", "", "nocode")}} represents a string that a developer can insert into an injection sink that will parse it as a URL of an external script. These objects are created via and therefore have no constructor.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TrustedTypePolicy
files.Summary: The TrustedTypePolicy interface of the {{domxref("Trusted Types API", "", "", "nocode")}} defines a group of functions which create TrustedType objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.TrustedTypePolicyFactory
files.Summary: The TrustedTypePolicyFactory interface of the {{domxref("Trusted Types API", "", "", "nocode")}} creates policies and allows the verification of Trusted Type objects against created policies.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.UIEvent
files.Summary: The UIEvent interface represents simple user interface events.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.URL
files.Summary: The URL interface is used to parse, construct, normalize, and encode URL. It works by providing properties which allow you to easily read and modify the components of a URL.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.URLPattern
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The URLPattern interface of the {{domxref("URL Pattern API", "", "", "nocode")}} matches URLs or parts of URLs against a pattern. The pattern can contain capturing groups that extract parts of the matched URL.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.URLSearchParams
files.Summary: The URLSearchParams interface defines utility methods to work with the query string of a URL.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USB
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USB interface of the WebUSB API provides attributes and methods for finding and connecting USB devices from a web page.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USBAlternateInterface
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USBAlternateInterface interface of the WebUSB API provides information about a particular configuration of an interface provided by the USB device. An interface includes one or more alternate settings which can configure a set of endpoints based on the operating mode of the device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USBConfiguration
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USBConfiguration interface of the WebUSB API provides information about a particular configuration of a USB device and the interfaces that it supports.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USBConnectionEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USBConnectionEvent interface of the 'WebUSB API' is the event type passed to USBUSB.Connect_event and USB.Disconnect_event events when the user agent detects that a new USB device has been connected or disconnected.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USBDevice
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USBDevice interface of the WebUSB API provides access to metadata about a paired USB device and methods for controlling it.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USBEndpoint
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USBEndpoint interface of the WebUSB API provides information about an endpoint provided by the USB device. An endpoint represents a unidirectional data stream into or out of a device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USBInTransferResult
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USBInTransferResult interface of the WebUSB API provides the result from a call to the transferIn() and controlTransferIn() methods of the USBDevice interface. It represents the result from requesting a transfer of data from the USB device to the USB host.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USBInterface
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USBInterface interface of the WebUSB API provides information about an interface provided by the USB device. An interface represents a feature of the device which implements a particular protocol and may contain endpoints for bidirectional communication.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USBIsochronousInTransferPacket
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USBIsochronousInTransferPacket interface of the WebUSB API is part of the response from a call to the isochronousTransferIn() method of the USBDevice interface. It represents the status of an individual packet from a request to transfer data from the USB device to the USB host over an isochronous endpoint.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USBIsochronousInTransferResult
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USBIsochronousInTransferResult interface of the WebUSB API provides the result from a call to the isochronousTransferIn() method of the USBDevice interface. It represents the result from requesting a transfer of data from the USB device to the USB host.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USBIsochronousOutTransferPacket
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USBIsochronousOutTransferPacket interface of the WebUSB API is part of the response from a call to the isochronousTransferOut() method of the USBDevice interface. It represents the status of an individual packet from a request to transfer data from the USB host to the USB device over an isochronous endpoint.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USBIsochronousOutTransferResult
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USBIsochronousOutTransferResult interface of the WebUSB API provides the result from a call to the isochronousTransferOut() method of the USBDevice interface. It represents the result from requesting a transfer of data from the USB host to the USB device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.USBOutTransferResult
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The USBOutTransferResult interface of the WebUSB API provides the result from a call to the transferOut() and controlTransferOut() methods of the USBDevice interface. It represents the result from requesting a transfer of data from the USB host to the USB device.
