files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.UserActivation
files.Summary: The UserActivation interface provides information about whether a user is currently interacting with the page, or has completed an interaction since page load.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.VTTCue
files.Summary: The VTTCue interface of the WebVTT API represents a cue that can be added to the text track associated with a particular video (or other media).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.VTTRegion
files.Summary: The VTTRegion interface of the WebVTT API describes a portion of the video to render a onto.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ValidityState
files.Summary: The ValidityState interface represents the validity states that an element can be in, with respect to constraint validation. Together, they help explain why an element's value fails to validate, if it's not valid.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.VideoColorSpace
files.Summary: The VideoColorSpace interface of the 'WebCodecs API' represents the color space of a video.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.VideoDecoder
files.Summary: The VideoDecoder interface of the 'WebCodecs API' decodes chunks of video.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.VideoEncoder
files.Summary: The VideoEncoder interface of the 'WebCodecs API' encodes objects into s.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.VideoFrame
files.Summary: The VideoFrame interface of the Web Codecs API represents a frame of a video.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.VideoPlaybackQuality
files.Summary: A VideoPlaybackQuality object is returned by the method and contains metrics that can be used to determine the playback quality of a video.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.VideoTrack
files.Summary: The VideoTrack interface represents a single video track from a video element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.VideoTrackList
files.Summary: The VideoTrackList interface is used to represent a list of the video tracks contained within a {{HTMLElement("video")}} element, with each track represented by a separate object in the list.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ViewTimeline
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The ViewTimeline interface of the {{domxref("Web Animations API", "Web Animations API", "", "nocode")}} represents a view progress timeline (see CSS scroll-driven animations for more details).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.ViewTransition
files.Summary: The ViewTransition interface of the {{domxref("View Transition API", "View Transition API", "", "nocode")}} represents an active view transition, and provides functionality to react to the transition reaching different states (e.g. ready to run the animation, or animation finished) or skip the transition altogether.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.VirtualKeyboard
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The VirtualKeyboard interface of the VirtualKeyboard API is useful on devices that have on-screen virtual keyboards, such as tablets, mobile phones, or other devices where a hardware keyboard may not be available.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.VisibilityStateEntry
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The VisibilityStateEntry interface provides timings of page visibility state changes, i.e., when a tab changes from the foreground to the background or vice versa.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.VisualViewport
files.Summary: The VisualViewport interface of the {{domxref("Visual Viewport API", "", "", "nocode")}} represents the visual viewport for a given window. For a page containing iframes, each iframe, as well as the containing page, will have a unique window object. Each window on a page will have a unique VisualViewport representing the properties associated with that window.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WGSLLanguageFeatures
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The WGSLLanguageFeatures interface of the {{domxref("WebGPU API", "WebGPU API", "", "nocode")}} is a setlike object that reports the WGSL language extensions supported by the WebGPU implementation.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WakeLock
files.Summary: The WakeLock interface of the Screen Wake Lock API can be used to request a lock that prevents device screens from dimming or locking when an application needs to keep running.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WakeLockSentinel
files.Summary: The WakeLockSentinel interface of the Screen Wake Lock API can be used to monitor the status of the platform screen wake lock, and manually release the lock when needed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WaveShaperNode
files.Summary: The WaveShaperNode interface represents a non-linear distorter.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGL2RenderingContext
files.Summary: The WebGL2RenderingContext interface provides the OpenGL ES 3.0 rendering context for the drawing surface of an HTML canvas element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLActiveInfo
files.Summary: The WebGLActiveInfo interface is part of the WebGL API and represents the information returned by calling the WebGLRenderingContext.GetActiveAttrib and WebGLRenderingContext.GetActiveUniform methods.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLBuffer
files.Summary: The WebGLBuffer interface is part of the WebGL API and represents an opaque buffer object storing data such as vertices or colors.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLContextEvent
files.Summary: The WebGLContextEvent interface is part of the WebGL API and is an interface for an event that is generated in response to a status change to the WebGL rendering context.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLFramebuffer
files.Summary: The WebGLFramebuffer interface is part of the WebGL API and represents a collection of buffers that serve as a rendering destination.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLObject
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The WebGLObject is part of the WebGL API and is the parent interface for all WebGL objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLProgram
files.Summary: The WebGLProgram is part of the WebGL API and is a combination of two compiled s consisting of a vertex shader and a fragment shader (both written in GLSL).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLQuery
files.Summary: The WebGLQuery interface is part of the WebGL 2 API and provides ways to asynchronously query for information. By default, occlusion queries and primitive queries are available.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLRenderbuffer
files.Summary: The WebGLRenderbuffer interface is part of the WebGL API and represents a buffer that can contain an image, or that can be a source or target of a rendering operation.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLRenderingContext
files.Summary: The WebGLRenderingContext interface provides an interface to the OpenGL ES 2.0 graphics rendering context for the drawing surface of an HTML canvas element.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLSampler
files.Summary: The WebGLSampler interface is part of the WebGL 2 API and stores sampling parameters for access inside of a shader.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLShader
files.Summary: The WebGLShader is part of the WebGL API and can either be a vertex or a fragment shader. A requires both types of shaders.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat
files.Summary: The WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat interface is part of the WebGL API and represents the information returned by calling the WebGLRenderingContext.GetShaderPrecisionFormat method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLSync
files.Summary: The WebGLSync interface is part of the WebGL 2 API and is used to synchronize activities between the GPU and the application.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLTexture
files.Summary: The WebGLTexture interface is part of the WebGL API and represents an opaque texture object providing storage and state for texturing operations.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLTransformFeedback
files.Summary: The WebGLTransformFeedback interface is part of the WebGL 2 API and enables transform feedback, which is the process of capturing primitives generated by vertex processing. It allows to preserve the post-transform rendering state of an object and resubmit this data multiple times.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLUniformLocation
files.Summary: The WebGLUniformLocation interface is part of the WebGL API and represents the location of a uniform variable in a shader program.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebGLVertexArrayObject
files.Summary: The WebGLVertexArrayObject interface is part of the WebGL 2 API, represents vertex array objects (VAOs) pointing to vertex array data, and provides names for different sets of vertex data.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebSocket
files.Summary: The WebSocket object provides the API for creating and managing a WebSocket connection to a server, as well as for sending and receiving data on the connection.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebTransport
files.Summary: The WebTransport interface of the {{domxref("WebTransport API", "WebTransport API", "", "nocode")}} provides functionality to enable a user agent to connect to an HTTP/3 server, initiate reliable and unreliable transport in either or both directions, and close the connection once it is no longer needed.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebTransportBidirectionalStream
files.Summary: The WebTransportBidirectionalStream interface of the {{domxref("WebTransport API", "WebTransport API", "", "nocode")}} represents a bidirectional stream created by a server or a client that can be used for reliable transport. Provides access to a for reading incoming data, and a for writing outgoing data.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebTransportCongestionControl
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The congestionControl read-only property of the interface indicates the application's preference for either high throughput or low-latency when sending data.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebTransportDatagramDuplexStream
files.Summary: The WebTransportDatagramDuplexStream interface of the {{domxref("WebTransport API", "WebTransport API", "", "nocode")}} represents a duplex stream that can be used for unreliable transport of datagrams between client and server. Provides access to a for reading incoming datagrams, a for writing outgoing datagrams, and various settings and statistics related to the stream.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebTransportError
files.Summary: The WebTransportError interface of the {{domxref("WebTransport API", "WebTransport API", "", "nocode")}} represents an error related to the API, which can arise from server errors, network connection problems, or client-initiated abort operations (for example, arising from a call).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebTransportErrorSource
files.Summary: The source read-only property of the interface returns an enumerated value indicating the source of the error.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebTransportReceiveStream
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The WebTransportReceiveStream interface of the {{domxref("WebTransport API", "WebTransport API", "", "nocode")}} is a that can be used to read from an incoming unidirectional or bidirectional stream.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WebTransportSendStream
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The WebTransportSendStream interface of the {{domxref("WebTransport API", "WebTransport API", "", "nocode")}} is a specialized that is used to send outbound data in both unidirectional or bidirectional streams.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WheelEvent
files.Summary: The WheelEvent interface represents events that occur due to the user moving a mouse wheel or similar input device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Window
files.Summary: The Window interface represents a window containing a DOM document; the document property points to the DOM document loaded in that window.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WindowClient
files.Summary: The WindowClient interface of the ServiceWorker API represents the scope of a service worker client that is a document in a browsing context, controlled by an active worker. The service worker client independently selects and uses a service worker for its own loading and sub-resources.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WindowControlsOverlay
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The WindowControlsOverlay interface of the Window Controls Overlay API exposes information about the geometry
of the title bar area in desktop Progressive Web Apps, and an event to know whenever it changes. This interface is accessible from 'Navigator.WindowControlsOverlay'.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WindowControlsOverlayGeometryChangeEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The WindowControlsOverlayGeometryChangeEvent interface of the Window Controls Overlay API is passed to WindowControlsOverlay/geometrychange_event when the size or visibility of a desktop Progress Web App's title bar region changes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WindowLocalStorage
files.Summary: The localStorage read-only property of the interface allows you to access a object for the 's {{glossary("origin")}}; the stored data is saved across browser sessions.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WindowSessionStorage
files.Summary:
The read-only sessionStorage
property accesses a session object for the current
origin. sessionStorage is similar to
Window.LocalStorage; the difference is that while data
in localStorage doesn't expire, data in sessionStorage is
cleared when the page session ends.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WindowSharedStorage
files.Summary: The WindowSharedStorage interface of the {{domxref("Shared Storage API", "Shared Storage API", "", "nocode")}} represents the shared storage for a particular origin within a standard browsing context.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Worker
files.Summary: The Worker interface of the Web Workers API represents a background task that can be created via script, which can send messages back to its creator.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WorkerGlobalScope
files.Summary: The WorkerGlobalScope interface of the Web Workers API is an interface representing the scope of any worker. Workers have no browsing context; this scope contains the information usually conveyed by objects in this case event handlers, the console or the associated object. Each WorkerGlobalScope has its own event loop.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WorkerLocation
files.Summary: The WorkerLocation interface defines the absolute location of the script executed by the . Such an object is initialized for each worker and is available via the property obtained by calling self.location.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WorkerNavigator
files.Summary: The WorkerNavigator interface represents a subset of the interface allowed to be accessed from a . Such an object is initialized for each worker and is available via the property.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.Worklet
files.Summary: The Worklet interface is a lightweight version of Web Workers and gives developers access to low-level parts of the rendering pipeline.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WorkletGlobalScope
files.Summary: The WorkletGlobalScope interface is an abstract class that specific worklet scope classes inherit from. Each WorkletGlobalScope defines a new global environment.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WorkletSharedStorage
files.Summary: The WorkletSharedStorage interface of the {{domxref("Shared Storage API", "Shared Storage API", "", "nocode")}} represents the shared storage for a particular origin within a worklet context.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WritableStream
files.Summary:
The WritableStream interface of the Streams API provides a standard abstraction for writing streaming data to a destination, known as a sink.
This object comes with built-in backpressure and queuing.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WritableStreamDefaultController
files.Summary: The WritableStreamDefaultController interface of the Streams API represents a controller allowing control of a 's state. When constructing a WritableStream, the underlying sink is given a corresponding WritableStreamDefaultController instance to manipulate.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.WritableStreamDefaultWriter
files.Summary: The WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface of the Streams API is the object returned by and once created locks the writer to the WritableStream ensuring that no other streams can write to the underlying sink.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XMLDocument
files.Summary: The XMLDocument interface represents an XML document. It inherits from the generic and does not add any specific methods or properties to it: nevertheless, several algorithms behave differently with the two types of documents.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XMLHttpRequest
files.Summary: XMLHttpRequest (XHR) objects are used to interact with servers. You can retrieve data from a URL without having to do a full page refresh. This enables a Web page to update just part of a page without disrupting what the user is doing.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XMLHttpRequestEventTarget
files.Summary: XMLHttpRequestEventTarget is the interface that describes the event handlers shared on and .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XMLHttpRequestResponseType
files.Summary:
The property
responseType is an enumerated string value specifying
the type of data contained in the response.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XMLHttpRequestUpload
files.Summary: The XMLHttpRequestUpload interface represents the upload process for a specific . It is an opaque object that represents the underlying, browser-dependent, upload process. It is an and can be obtained by calling .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XMLSerializer
files.Summary: The XMLSerializer interface provides the method to construct an XML string representing a {{Glossary("DOM")}} tree.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XPathEvaluator
files.Summary: The XPathEvaluator interface allows to compile and evaluate XPath expressions.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XPathExpression
files.Summary: This is useful when an expression will be reused in an application, because it is just compiled once and all namespace prefixes which occur within the expression are preresolved.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XPathResult
files.Summary: The XPathResult interface represents the results generated by evaluating an XPath expression within the context of a given node.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRAnchor
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRAnchor interface creates anchors which keep track of the pose that is fixed relative to the real world. With anchors, you can specify poses in the world that need to be updated to correctly reflect the evolving understanding of the world, such that the poses remain aligned with the same place in the physical world. That helps to build an illusion that the placed objects are really present in the user's environment.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRAnchorSet
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRAnchorSet interface exposes a collection of anchors. Its instances are returned by and are Set-like objects.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRBoundedReferenceSpace
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The WebXR Device API's XRBoundedReferenceSpace interface describes a virtual world reference space which has preset boundaries. This extends , which describes an essentially unrestricted space around the viewer's position. These bounds are defined using an array of points, each of which defines a vertex in a polygon inside which the user is allowed to move.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRCPUDepthInformation
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRCPUDepthInformation interface contains depth information from the CPU (returned by ).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRCompositionLayer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRCompositionLayer interface of the WebXR Device API is a base class that defines a set of common properties and behaviors for WebXR layer types. It is not constructable on its own.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRCubeLayer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRCubeLayer interface of the WebXR Device API is a layer that renders directly from a cubemap and projects it onto the inside faces of a cube.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRCylinderLayer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRCylinderLayer interface of the WebXR Device API is a layer that takes up a curved rectangular space in the virtual environment. Only the front of the layer is visible.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRDepthInformation
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRDepthInformation interface contains information about the distance from the user's device to the real-world geometry in the user's environment.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XREquirectLayer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XREquirectLayer interface of the WebXR Device API is a layer that maps equirectangular coded data onto the inside of a sphere.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRFrame
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
A WebXR Device APIXRFrame object is passed into the callback function and provides access to the information needed in order to render a single frame of animation for an describing a VR or AR scene. Events which communicate the tracking state of objects also provide an XRFrame reference as part of their structure.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRHand
files.Summary: The XRHand interface is pair iterator (an ordered map) with the key being the hand joints and the value being an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRHitTestResult
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRHitTestResult interface of the WebXR Device API contains a single result of a hit test. You can get an array of XRHitTestResult objects for a frame by calling .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRHitTestSource
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRHitTestSource interface of the WebXR Device API handles hit test subscriptions. You can get an XRHitTestSource object by using the method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRInputSource
files.Summary: The WebXR Device API'sXRInputSource interface describes a single source of control input which is part of the user's WebXR-compatible virtual or augmented reality system. The device is specific to the platform being used, but provides the direction in which it is being aimed and optionally may generate events if the user triggers performs actions using the device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRInputSourceArray
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The interface XRInputSourceArray represents a live list of WebXR input sources, and is used as the return value of the property . Each entry is an representing one input device connected to the WebXR system.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRInputSourceEvent
files.Summary: The WebXR Device API's XRInputSourceEvent interface describes an event which has occurred on a WebXR user input device such as a hand controller, gaze tracking system, or motion tracking system. More specifically, they represent a change in the state of an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRInputSourcesChangeEvent
files.Summary: The WebXR Device API interface XRInputSourcesChangeEvent is used to represent the XRSession.Inputsourceschange_event event sent to an when the set of available WebXR input controllers changes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRJointPose
files.Summary: The XRJointPose interface is an with additional information about the size of the skeleton joint it represents.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRJointSpace
files.Summary: The XRJointSpace interface is an and represents the position and orientation of an joint.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRLayer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRLayer interface of the WebXR Device API is the base class for WebXR layer types. It inherits methods from .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRLayerEvent
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRLayerEvent interface of the WebXR Device API is the event type for events related to a change of state of an object. These events occur, for example, when the layer needs to be redrawn.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRLightEstimate
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRLightEstimate interface of the WebXR Device API provides the estimated lighting values for an at the time represented by an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRLightProbe
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRLightProbe interface of the WebXR Device API contains lighting information at a given point in the user's environment. You can get an XRLighting object using the method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRMediaBinding
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRMediaBinding interface is used to create layers that display the content of an .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRPose
files.Summary: XRPose is a WebXR API interface representing a position and orientation in the 3D space, relative to the within which it resides. The XRSpacewhich is either an or an defines the coordinate system used for the pose and, in the case of an , its underlying views.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRProjectionLayer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRProjectionLayer interface of the WebXR Device API is a layer that fills the entire view of the observer and is refreshed close to the device's native frame rate.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRQuadLayer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRQuadLayer interface of the WebXR Device API is a layer that takes up a flat rectangular space in the virtual environment. An XRQuadLayer has no thickness. It is a two-dimensional object positioned and oriented in 3D space. The position of a quad refers to the center of the quad. Only the front of the layer is visible.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRRay
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRRay interface of the WebXR Device API is a geometric ray described by an origin point and a direction vector.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRReferenceSpace
files.Summary: The WebXR Device API's XRReferenceSpace interface describes the coordinate system for a specific tracked entity or object within the virtual world using a specified tracking behavior. The tracking behavior is defined by the selected reference space type. It expands upon the base class, , by adding support for several different tracking behaviors as well as to request a new reference space which describes the offset transform between the tracked object and another location in the world.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRReferenceSpaceEvent
files.Summary: The WebXR Device API interface XRReferenceSpaceEvent represents an event sent to an . Currently, the only event that uses this type is the XRReferenceSpace.Reset_event event.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRRenderState
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRRenderState interface of the WebXR Device API contains configurable values which affect how the imagery generated by an gets composited. These properties include the range of distances from the viewer within which content should be rendered, the vertical field of view (for inline presentations), and a reference to the being used as the target for rendering the scene prior to it being presented on the XR device's display or displays.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRRigidTransform
files.Summary: The XRRigidTransform is a WebXR API interface that represents the 3D geometric transform described by a position and orientation.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRSession
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRSession interface of the WebXR Device API represents an ongoing XR session, providing methods and properties used to interact with and control the session. To open a WebXR session, use the interface's method.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRSessionEvent
files.Summary: The WebXR Device API's XRSessionEvent interface describes an event which indicates the change of the state of an . These events occur, for example, when the session ends or the visibility of its context changes.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRSpace
files.Summary: The XRSpace interface of the WebXR Device API is an abstract interface providing a common basis for every class which represents a virtual coordinate system within the virtual world, in which its origin corresponds to a physical location. Spatial data in WebXR is always expressed relative to an object based upon one of the descendant interfaces of XRSpace, at the time at which a given takes place.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRSubImage
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRSubImage interface of the WebXR Device API represents what viewport of the GPU texture to use for rendering.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRSystem
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The WebXR Device API interface XRSystem provides methods which let you get access to an object representing a WebXR session. With that XRSession in hand, you can use it to interact with the Augmented Reality (AR) or Virtual Reality (VR) device.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRTransientInputHitTestResult
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRTransientInputHitTestResult interface of the WebXR Device API contains an array of results of a hit test for transient input, grouped by input source.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRTransientInputHitTestSource
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRTransientInputHitTestSource interface of the WebXR Device API handles transient input hit test subscriptions. You can get an XRTransientInputHitTestSource object by calling the .

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRView
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The WebXR Device API's XRView interface describes a single view into the XR scene for a specific frame, providing orientation and position information for the viewpoint. You can think of it as a description of a specific eye or camera and how it views the world. A 3D frame will involve two views, one for each eye, separated by an appropriate distance which approximates the distance between the viewer's eyes. This allows the two views, when projected in isolation into the appropriate eyes, to simulate a 3D world.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRViewerPose
files.Summary: The WebXR Device API interface XRViewerPose represents the pose (the position and orientation) of a viewer's point of view on the scene. Each XRViewerPose can have multiple views to represent, for example, the slight separation between the left and right eye.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRViewport
files.Summary: The WebXR Device API's XRViewport interface provides properties used to describe the size and position of the current viewport within the being used to render the 3D scene.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRWebGLBinding
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRWebGLBinding interface is used to create layers that have a GPU backend.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRWebGLDepthInformation
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRWebGLDepthInformation interface contains depth information from the GPU/WebGL (returned by ).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRWebGLLayer
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRWebGLLayer interface of the WebXR Device API provides a linkage between the WebXR device (or simulated XR device, in the case of an inline session) and a WebGL context used to render the scene for display on the device. In particular, it provides access to the WebGL framebuffer and viewport to ease access to the context.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XRWebGLSubImage
files.Summary:
NOTE
Experimental
The XRWebGLSubImage interface is used during rendering of WebGL layers.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.XSLTProcessor
files.Summary:
An XSLTProcessor applies an XSLT stylesheet transformation to an XML document to
produce a new XML document as output. It has methods to load the XSLT stylesheet, to
manipulate <xsl:param> parameter values, and to apply the
transformation to documents.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.APIs.JS.console
files.Summary: The console object provides access to the debugging console (e.g., the Web console in Firefox).

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.CSTOJS
files.Summary: Main type for CSharpToJavaScript.

files.Title: CSharpToJavaScript.CSTOJSOptions
files.Summary: Options for .
